title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: Mix together the flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into a greased deep dish baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Allow to cool completely.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on pastry.

title: mozzarella in carrozza(mozzarella in a carriage)
directions: Slice bread across into 1/2-inch slices.
Slice cheese into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Beat eggs in a bowl; soak each slice of bread in eggs.
Place in hot oil; brown lightly on each side.
Place bread slices on cookie sheet.
Place 1 slice of cheese on half of fried bread slices; cover with second slice.
Preheat oven to 350°. Place in heated oven until cheese is melted.
Make as many as needed.
Usually, 1 to 2 are enough if served with side dishes. Makes great brunch or lunch.

title: honey-glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrot pieces in 1-cup boiling water with salt in a medium saucepan 10 minutes or until tender; drain carrots and place in a serving bowl. Stir together orange juice and cornstarch in a small saucepan until smooth. Stir in butter and honey; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 4 minutes or until thickened. Pour over carrots and toss to coat. Yield: 4 servings.

title: divine potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk and cream cheese in saucepan until smooth. Add potatoes and onions.
Pour into 2-quart oblong buttered casserole.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Remove and top with cheese.
Return for 5 to 7 minutes to melt cheese.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil 3 peeled sweet potatoes in water with pinch of salt until tender. Add butter and mash while still hot.
Add all spices and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in sugar; add egg yolks, beating well after.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until pie is set and lightly browned.

title: easy enchilada pie
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Remove skillet from heat.
Stir together soup and milk.
Spoon half of soup mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut tortillas in half.
Use 8 halves to place over soup in dish.
Spoon meat mixture over tortillas.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Spoon remaining soup over tortillas. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with salsa.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, garlic salt, and onions until creamy.
Cut crust off bread.
Spread cheese mixture on bread and cut into 3 strips.
Cut bacon into fourths.
Roll each piece of bacon around each strip of bread and secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
(These can be frozen before baked.)

title: shredded beef dip
directions: Rinse beef under running water to rinse off salt.
Shred into small pieces. Mix cream cheese, sour cream, milk and beef.
Add onion and ripe olives.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crisp, raw vegetables as dippers.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Butter bottom of square baking dish.
Put rice, onion soup mix package, mushroom soup and water into baking dish.
Gently mix together.
Place pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Cover with tinfoil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for another 15 minutes at 400° to brown pork chops.
Cooking time is 1 hour!
Dirty dishes!!

title: catalina green beans
directions: Place whole green beans in baking dish.
Arrange bacon on top of green beans.
Pour Catalina dressing over this.
Do not cover completely.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs using mixer at medium speed.
Reduce speed and add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add sour cream.
Add flavoring.

title: homemade white bread
directions: Combine yeast, honey and 1/2 cup of milk together until yeast is dissolved.
Place rest of milk, butter and salt in bowl.
Add yeast mixture to bowl and add flour.
Knead dough for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place kneaded dough in buttered bowl and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down and knead 5 minutes.
Divide dough in half and shape into loaves.
Place dough in 2 buttered loaf pans and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Slash loaves with a razor and brush with water.
Bake at 400° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Combine warm milk, 1/4 cup sugar and butter or oleo.
Dissolve yeast, water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Combine yeast and milk mixtures.
Add well beaten egg.
Blend in flour well into mixture. Turn on lightly floured surface and knead 2 minutes.
Allow dough to rest 15 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Combine and sprinkle dough with brown sugar, 3 tablespoons white sugar and cinnamon.
Roll and place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water and all food coloring.
Let partially jell and add remaining ingredients.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk together for 6 minutes.
Put chocolate, Marshmallow Creme and nuts in a large bowl.
Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl.
Beat until chocolate is all melted.
Pour into a lightly greased pan or platters.
Let stand at least 4 to 6 hours before cutting.
Store in tin box.

title: peanut brittle in microwave
directions: In 2-quart glass dish, microwave the following:
peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt on High for 4 minutes (no lid).
Stir and microwave 4 more minutes.
Put in soda and stir quickly until foamy.
Put on cookie sheet and spread out quickly.
Cool and break apart.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together in the order given.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: granny's sweet potatoes
directions: Step 1:
Mix flour, 1 stick butter or margarine and chopped pecans and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until brown.
Let cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve with fresh fruit.
(Delicious.)

title: marseillaise bouillabaisse
directions: The dish requires certain fish that are obtainable only in France.
However, even with substitutes, you will find it excellent and unique.
In a large casserole, heat the oil.
Add the onions, tomatoes and garlic.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the bay leaf, salt, saffron, pepper, fish and boiling water.
The more different kinds of fish you have, the better the results will be.
Add the lobster and cook for 10 minutes.
Add the shrimp and wine; stir gently so as not to break up the fish and cook for 10 more minutes.
Correct the seasoning, bearing in mind that the dish should be fairly spicy.
Prepare individual soup plates for each person.
Place pieces of fish, lobster and shrimp in each plate and pour the soup on top.
Serve with toasted French bread.

title: carrot bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange carrots in ungreased baking dish. Layer cauliflower over carrots.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and nutmeg.
Cover and bake until vegetables are tender (50 to 55 minutes).
Sprinkle with cheese and garnish with parsley.

title: floor cleaner
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pail.
Mop small areas at a time with a minimum of liquid.
Safe for all tile and linoleum floors, but don't use on cork or wooden floors.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy saucepan, heat sugar, syrup, water and salt to 290° using candy thermometer.
Add peanuts.
Reduce heat to medium and stir constantly.
Cook until syrup spins a thread 300° on thermometer, add butter, then baking soda.
Beat rapidly with spoon and pour on a buttered surface, spreading 1/4 inch thick.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and garlic; cook for 4 to 5 minutes. Blend mustard and sugar.
Add to pan, along with remaining ingredients, except ribs.
Bring to a boil.
Salt ribs and place, bone side down, on grill over slow coals.
Broil 20 minutes; turn and brown other side.
Turn, meat side up, and broil 20 minutes longer.
Brush meat side with sauce and continue to broil 20 to 30 minutes, until done.
Baste occasionally.
Brush sauce on both sides of ribs; broil 2 to 3 minutes for a fine finishing.

title: 5 hour or theology stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole with a tight lid.
Cook for 5 hours at 275°.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Bring to boil the butter and water; cool slightly. Add 1 cup flour; add eggs, one at a time and beat well. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil,
bone
and
tear apart chicken.
Combine chicken, celery soup
and mayonnaise.
Put rice in bottom of casserole dish. (Also
a little broth.) Put chicken combination on top. Cook approximately
30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Put noodles on top to serve.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix gently with hands.
Roll out, when smooth, into flat pan, 1/4-inch thick, or cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar.
Store in an airtight container.

title: arugela salad
directions: Wash Arugela well.
Pat dry.
Chop coarsely.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix olive oil and lemon juice well and dress salad.
Toss lightly.
Serves 4.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Brown flour in oil to make a roux. Add next 4 ingredients. Cook until tender. Pour mixture into 1 gallon simmering water. Stir well, adding next 4 items. Boil slowly 2 1/2 hours. Add shrimp and crab; cook 1/2 hour. Add oysters for last 10 minutes. Serve over rice in soup bowls. Serves 14 to 16.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat. Add sauce and water; simmer about 10 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients except noodles. Pour about 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 baking pan. Layer 3 pieces uncooked noodles over sauce. Cover with about 1 1/2 cups sauce. Spread half of cheese mixture over sauce. Repeat layers. Top with layer of lasagna and sauce. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Remove foil. Bake 10 more minutes. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: creamy ham and chicken medley
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in large saucepan over medium heat; add mushrooms and cook until tender, stirring constantly.
Remove from saucepan; set aside.
Melt 1/3 cup butter in saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add 2 1/2 cups milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in whipping cream and next 5 ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts and mixture is smooth; stir in ham and chicken.
Add enough of remaining 1/2 cup milk for a thinner consistency, if desired.
To serve, spoon into shells and sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 12 servings.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese, milk and confectioners sugar, then add Cool Whip.
Break cake into little bites.
Put this in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cake.
Pour strawberries and strawberry glaze over cake and Cool Whip mixture. Let get cold before serving.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dip breasts into beaten eggs, then the crumb mixture.
Brown lightly in hot oil.
Put a small amount of spaghetti sauce in baking dish.
Lay the breasts on sauce.
Put a small amount of sauce on each breast.
Sprinkle a little more Parmesan cheese over each.
Add some Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: aunt fannie's baked squash
directions: Wash squash and cut up into pieces.
Boil until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Add all but 1/2 of the margarine to squash.
Melt remaining margarine.
Pour squash mixture into baking dish, sprinkle with cracker meal and pour melted margarine on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bubbly and brown on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into small balls.
Heat tomato soup and water in pressure cooker.
Drop meatballs into soup mixture.
Place cover on cooker.
After starts giggling," cook 10 to 20 minutes at 15 pounds pressure.

title: grandma harris' soup
directions: Cut meat into small cubes.
Cook with chopped onion in 2 to 3 inches water until tender.
Chop and add potatoes and macaroni and cook on low heat until done.
Add remaining ingredients except rice and sugar.
Heat through.
Add rice and sugar, if desired, to taste.
Makes stew-like soup.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add alternately with cream.
Add flavorings.
Bake in tube pan (prepared with butter and flour).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or more, until well done.

title: shipwreck
directions: Slice potatoes in greased casserole and crumble beef on top. Sprinkle on the salt and pepper.
Slice onion and spread over the beef.
Spread kidney beans over the onion.
Cover all with undiluted tomato soup.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours in covered baking dish.

title: coconut pound cake(good)
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
Add coconut and coconut extract. Grease large tube pan; cook at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes, starting in cold oven.
Let cool in pan.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with crushed chips.
Mix rest on ingredients and spoon over.
Top with more chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with green onions and salsa.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; stir well.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce to low heat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Yields 3 cups.
Excellent!

title: wassail bowl
directions: Mix all together in pot; cook slowly for 1 hour.
Can simmer up to 4 hours.
Serves approximately 12 cups.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a small amount of oil.
Put in a shallow casserole and put 1/4-inch slice of lemon (rind and all) on top of each chop.

Add a scoop of cream of mushroom soup on top of the lemon, using the whole can of soup on top of the 6 pork chops. Fill the soup can 1/3 full with water and drizzle over chops. Cover and place in 350° oven for 1 hour.
(Lemon is also edible.)

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch, syrup, vanilla and cold water to a boil and cook until thick; remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and coloring.
Pour over fresh strawberries that have been placed in a baked pie shell.
Then top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Bring to a boil butter, cocoa and milk, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients and mix until blended.
Spread immediately on top of hot cake.
I start making my frosting about 3 or 4 minutes before the cake is done baking.
This fudge frosting tastes like fudge candy on top of a cake.

title: italian bread(quick and easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cut bread to, but not through, the bottom, into 12 slices. Place on a baking sheet. Combine cheese, salad dressing, basil, garlic powder, oregano and onion salt in a small bowl and mix well. Spread the mixture between slices and over top of bread. Bake about 12 minutes, until golden brown.

title: apple salad
directions: Add cinnamon to dry jello.
Add hot water to jello mix.
Add apple juice to jello mix.
Stir jello well; then add other ingredients and pour into dish and refrigerate.

title: kris kringle punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients into a punch bowl. Just before serving, pour in ginger ale and stir well.
Garnish with ice ring.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil. Drop mixture by tablespoons into 1/8-inch of hot oil.
Flatten patties to 1/4-inch thickness.
Turn and brown on other side.
Makes about 14.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch sheet cake pan.
Pour in cherry pie filling and sprinkle cake mix over it.
Put margarine slices on next.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: brine to cure ham or bacon
directions: Bring to boil and pour over meat.
Let stand in brine approximately 1 week for bacon and 2 weeks for ham.

title: crusty tuna surprise
directions: Combine cheese soup and milk.
In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange layers of rice, tuna, parsley and cheese soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Combine corn flake crumbs with margarine and sprinkle over tuna mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 425° about 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine ingredients and cook on low until mixture thickens. Cool and
pour over jello mixture; top with Cool Whip and let set for at least an hour before serving.

title: banana salad
directions: Beat egg until fluffy.
Add sugar and flour.
Beat well; add milk.
Cook until thick and add 3 tablespoons of peanut butter. Mix well and put in refrigerator to cool.
Place layer of dressing, then a layer of bananas.
Sprinkle with peanuts to serve.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: Saute onion in butter; stir in next 8 ingredients.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture on tortilla.
Roll and place seam side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: diet pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Add oil to pan.
Heat.
Add beef and cook about 5 minutes.
Then remove meat from oil.
Add celery, green peppers, onions and garlic.
Stir-fry these vegetables about 7 minutes.
Add bouillon, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Blend well, then add beef and cook until meat is tender.

title: jelled peach sauce
directions: Drain canned peaches, saving the syrup.
Puree the peaches in the blender.
To the drained peach syrup, add enough water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Pour into a saucepan and add the sugar and nutmeg.
Bring mixture to a boil and let it boil for about 1 minute.
Next, empty the box of gelatin into a bowl, and stir in the hot liquid mixture, until the gelatin is dissolved.
Add pureed peaches and pour into a mold.
Chill until set.

title: sauce for spaghetti
directions: Cook onion and garlic until tender in oil; do not scorch.
Add all ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Into this sauce, add the meatballs in the following recipe and serve over hot cooked spaghetti.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add butter or margarine and egg.
Crumble ingredients.
Use half the mixture and line a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: eggplant roma
directions: Put the boiled eggplant in a baking dish.
Place 1 slice of Provolone cheese on each.
Sprinkle with the baconettes.
Pour tomato sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Skin tomatoes by placing in hot water. Slice into large 4 quart container.
Slice onions and peppers into the container. Stir in sugar, vinegar, salt, red pepper and bag containing cinnamon
and
cloves.
Cook
slowly
a long time, about 3 hours, until
the sauce thickens.
Remove spice bag.
Place in sterile pint jars and seal.
Process 10 minutes.

title: brownie cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix brownies according to package directions.
Spread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and flavor.
Stir in Seven-Up.
Bake in well-greased floured Bundt pan at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: california rice
directions: Lightly grease 2-quart baking dish.
In hot butter in skillet, saute onion until golden.
Remove from heat; stir in rice and other ingredients with half of sharp cheese.
Toss lightly to mix well.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle rest of cheese on top. Bake uncovered 25 minutes at 375° or until hot and bubbly. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream Crisco, peanut butter and sugars, then add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove.
Add Kisses to top.
Bake 2 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix jello according to package directions.
Add vanilla ice cream to jello mixture while still warm.
Add one cup of crushed pineapple and the nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaf with club crackers.

title: super carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Then add other ingredients. Mix well by hand then pour into greased, floured pan and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until cake shrinks from side of pan. Makes a huge cake.
Very delicious.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Mix in other ingredients. Cook over medium-high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil and stir for exactly 2 1/2 minutes.
Set off and place pan in a sink about 1/4 full of cold water.
Beat until fudge starts to thicken.
Pour on greased plate.

title: snowball cake
directions: Break up angel food cake in small pieces.
Mix vanilla pudding and milk together about 2 minutes or until starts to get thick, then pour it over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding, then strawberry pie filling on top.
Chill and serve.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in large flat pan. Bake in 325° oven for 3 hours or until thick. Stir thoroughly every 15 to 20 minutes. Can in small jars.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add liquids.
Stir in chopped Milky Ways. Pour into ice cream freezer.

title: congealed salad (cherry)
directions: Mix and let congeal.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and peppers in butter.
Add chicken and soup.
Stir until hot.

title: light 'n easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground turkey and fennel seed in a large saucepan. Drain well and crumble.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water. Simmer, covered, until heated.
Combine cottage cheese and eggs in container of electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Stir in parsley.

title: pizza horns
directions: Thaw bread dough.
On lightly floured surface, roll into a 10-inch circle.
Brush with oil.
Cut each circle into 8 triangles or wedges.
Spread surface with pizza sauce, oregano and garlic powder; leave a 1/4-inch margin on each side.
Sprinkle with cheeses, green pepper and pepperoni.
Roll up each triangle, beginning from the wide end.
Place on oiled baking sheets.
Brush tops with egg white.
Sprinkle on additional oregano or Parmesan. Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice on low speed until crumbly.
Press on bottom of 15 x 10-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk, 2 eggs, 2 teaspoons spice and salt; mix well.
Pour over crust and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Chill; cut into bars and store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add pineapple.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring in mayonnaise last.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill for 3 hours before serving.

title: tomato cheese snacks
directions: Half the English muffins.
Slice tomatoes and place one on each muffin.
Place one slice cheese on top of tomatoes.
Add a little of the green onions on top of cheese.
Broil until cheese melts or turns brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bring to boil and cook 1 minute the water, oil, margarine and cocoa.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, buttermilk and salt and soda. Add cocoa mixture and add sugar and flour. Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easiest ever punch
directions: Scoop sherbet out into a punch bowl.
Pour the pineapple juice, ginger ale and Cheerwine over the sherbet and stir.

title: cream of broccoli soup with white wine(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In a large pot, bring 7 cups of chicken or vegetable stock to a boil.
Remove 1 cup and reserve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in top of double boiler over simmering hot water, stirring until smooth.
Add sugar and milk. Continue stirring over water until well blended.
Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons water.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.

title: zucchini and cheese casserole
directions: Boil together zucchini and onion.
Heat to almost boiling milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat egg and add to sauce.
Add sauce mixture to zucchini and onion.
Mix cheese, bread crumbs and chilies and layer with squash mixture in buttered dish.
Top layer should be cheese, bread crumbs and chilies.
Cook until bubbly.

title: fresh grapefruit cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with juice, beginning and ending with flour mix.
Gradually add milk.
Stir in peel and vanilla; mix well.

title: boned ham with dried fruit stuffing
directions: Make pocket in ham for stuffing.
Soak fruit in a bowl with water for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain and reserve water.
In a saucepan, place reserved water with sugar and cook for 5 minutes to dissolve.
Add lemon juice and cornstarch, cooking and stirring until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add rum, fruit and bread crumbs.
Mix well and stuff ham.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serves about 20.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine milk and next 7 ingredients; add to dry ingredients.
Pour mixture into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cranberry sauce in a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine oats, flour and brown sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cranberries.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 5 to 6 servings, each serving containing 345 calories, 10 grams fat (% from fat 26%), 26 milligrams cholesterol and 129 milligrams sodium.

title: quick pinto bean fudge
directions: Mash together first 3 ingredients to a mashed potato consistency.
Heat chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Pour hot chocolate mixture into the beans and stir until slightly thickened.
Work in powdered sugar.
Knead with hands and spread into a lightly buttered pan.
Refrigerate; candy will stay moist in refrigerator for a long time (if you can keep the family away from it).

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Cook till thick over medium-low heat. Cool.
Pour over fruit.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Line dish with crushed cornflakes.
Shred 4 cups cabbage and put over flakes.
Heat cream of celery soup, milk, mayonnaise and margarine.
Pour over cabbage.
Crush cornflakes over top; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mashed potato leftovers
directions: To 1 cup of mashed potatoes, add 1 egg yolk and 3 tablespoons flour.
Beat egg white until stiff and fold in.
Add parsley, if desired.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil until well browned. Makes many small puffy balls.

title: cranberry nut muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, beat eggs; add orange juice and vegetable oil.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Spoon into 12 greased or papered muffin cups. (Cups will be almost full.)
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend very well.
Store in refrigerator or freeze.

title: nut crescents(traditional czechoslovakian cookie)
directions: Combine sifted flour with butter, egg, sugar, salt and vanilla and pecans.
Work with hands until thoroughly mixed or process in a food processor.
Shape into crescents by taking heaping teaspoon of dough and rolling between palms of hands until 1 to 2-inches long. Place in lightly greased cookie sheet in shape of crescent.
Bake in 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Should not be brown on top.
Cool slightly and sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: apple fritters
directions: Heat 1 1/2 to 2-inches oil in an electric frying pan at 375°. Mix all ingredients together to form batter.
Drop by spoonfuls (about 9 to 12 at a time) into hot oil.
Fry 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels and shake in cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: cranberry cheese spread
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream, honey and cinnamon until smooth.
Spread onto serving dish or plate.
In bowl, stir cranberry sauce until it reaches spreading consistency. Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix, water and Eagle Brand milk.
Put into refrigerator.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: turkey, beef or chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse. Combine noodles and remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Mix well.
Pour into greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli, water and bouillon cubes 5 to 7 minutes.
Set aside.
Saute onion in butter.
Add flour to onion and butter. Stir in warm milk, as needed, until thickened.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted, then add broccoli mixture and stir until warm.

title: quaker oat choc-chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla;
beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and morsels and mix well.
Drop by tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then wire rack.

title: red wedding punch
directions: Combine
all ingredients except ginger ale and sherbet; fill ring
mold with mixture.
Freeze for ice.
When ready to serve, pour ginger ale and sherbet into bowl.
Float ice ring in punch.

title: turkey sausage and squash
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet; add sausage links and brown quickly.
Add wine, herbs de provence and garlic.
Cover the skillet and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables to sausage and steam them for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: kate's barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat.
Put in a crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onion; drain off fat.
Add bacon, onion and remaining ingredients to the crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: banana punch(serves 40, 4 ounces)
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Puree bananas in blender with lemon juice and a small amount of sugar water.
Add banana puree to sugar water.
Add orange juice and pineapple juice.
Mix well and pour into container and freeze. Thaw an hour or so before serving.
Thaw to slush and add ginger ale.

title: calico beans
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot and cook slowly until hot.
May put in heavy pan and simmer on stove until hot.
The longer you simmer, the better they taste.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix well and chill.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: mandarin steak
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Combine orange juice and next 3 ingredients in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish; add steak, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate 10 minutes.
Remove steak from marinade, reserving 1/4 cup marinade.
Place steak on a rack in a roasting pan coated with cooking spray.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat 5 minutes.
Turn steak and broil an additional 2 minutes. Top steak with green onions; broil 2 minutes or to desired degree of doneness.
Slice steak diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch slices.
Place steak and onions on a serving platter; set aside and keep warm.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat strawberries, sugar and jello just enough to dissolve jello, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Mix pudding and milk by directions on box.
Add sour cream.
Fold in 3/4 ounces Cool Whip.

title: homemade potato chips
directions: Peel and slice potatoes real thin and salt.
Drop into hot cooking oil and brown.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl, combine the beef, egg white, onion, cracker crumbs, milk, salt and pepper.
Shape into four oval patties.
Fry in skillet over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes or until cooked through, turning once.
Remove patties and keep warm. Add gravy, mushrooms and water to skillet.
Heat 3 to 5 minutes. Serve over patties and noodles.

title: owens country lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles per package instructions.
Brown sausage, onion, and green pepper.
Drain excess oil.
Add garlic and creamed corn and heat thoroughly.
Put frozen peas in a colander and rinse to separate.

Place layer of noodles in a large 9 x 12-inch buttered casserole dish, then a layer of meat mixture. Pour 1/3 of tomato sauce over meat, sprinkle 1/3 of the peas over sauce and top with 1/3 of the cheese.
Repeat with two more layers, ending with a layer of cheese, then bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 4 to 6 as a main course.
Garnish with parsley or other green.

title: corn souffle
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 400° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes. Make sure you get a good rise.

title: sweet potato pie(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter; mix well. Add all other ingredients. Stir well. Pour in pie shell. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch).
Beat all ingredients until smooth; pour into pie plate.
Bake for about 30 minutes, or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into casserole dish.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put in nuts and coconut to keep sweet potatoes from turning dark.
Put in milk as soon as you grate.
Mix together.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old-time 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Combine milk and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients and the milk alternately to the egg-butter mixture.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna.
Break into large pieces.
Combine all ingredients except lettuce and sliced egg.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with egg slices.
Serves 6.

title: the best brisket
directions: Spray roasting pan with cooking spray.
Place sliced onions in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with Adolph's, pepper and garlic on both sides and prick meat all over with fork.
Place on top of onions with fat up, if there is any.
Pack top and sides of meat with brown sugar.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, but strawberries, in a pan.
Bring to a boil, then set off heat and let cool completely.
Bake pie shell and let cool.
Line pie shell with fresh strawberries.
Pour cooled mixture over strawberries and let chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs.
Add bananas.
Beat well.
Add flour sifted with baking soda and salt; add walnuts.
Bake 40 or 50 minutes in bread tin in a 350° oven. Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; gently fold blueberries into mixture.
Spoon into bottom of pie crust.
Dot mixture with butter, then cover with upper crust.
Sprinkle pie crust with sugar if desired.
Cut several slits in crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until crust is light brown.

title: nappa salad
directions: Break noodles apart and add to shredded cabbage.
Brown almonds in 3/4 cup stick oleo until lightly brown.
Cool.
Add to cabbage.
Mix and pour over salad:

title: impossible pie(sugar-free)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour into pie pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until lightly brown.
Allow to cool before serving.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs in Eagle Brand milk, stirring well after each.
Add pudding mix and stir well.
Add bananas and strawberries and vanilla and stir well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and fill to the top with whole milk.
Freeze accordingly.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake by directions and pour half batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with oleo and milk.
Blend all well and pour over cake in pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup nuts and chocolate chips over caramel mixture.
Pour remaining batter over all and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes longer and test for doneness.
Cut into squares.

title: pleasing potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well in a mixing bowl.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased hot skillet.
Take the rolled patty mixture and drop into the pan.
Turn the heat to medium.
Cook on both sides until lightly browned.
Repeat the process.
Turn each one over with a spatula.
Do this until it is golden brown and crispy.
Drain the grease off and serve.
Ready to eat. Delicious!

title: no toss layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, bell pepper, bacon and peas.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Spread mayonnaise on top of sugar.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Do not toss.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sugar-free chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Seal pie crust with beaten egg yolk.
Heat 5 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Beat milk and peanut butter until blended.
Add sugar-free instant chocolate pudding pie mix.	Beat 1 minute on low speed. Pour into cooled graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, top with low-fat Cool Whip.
Cut into 8 pieces.
Can be frozen and eat one piece at a time.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
In a double boiler, beat egg yolks slightly.
Add reserved syrup, sugar, vinegar and oleo.
Stir until thick.
Cool.

title: kuchen
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, yeast, flour and salt.
Blend well.
Let rise until double.
Spoon into 4 greased bread pans.
Brush with 1 beaten egg white, then add topping.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Spread 1 side of each tortilla with 1 1/2 teaspoons of sour cream.
Top 1/2 of tortillas with diced chicken; dot evenly with salsa, cheese and cilantro.
Top with remaining sour cream; fold over.
Place (sour cream side down) on microwave-safe plate and cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, until cheese is melted and quesadillas are hot through and through.
Repeat, then cut into 4 to 6 wedges.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain and save for topping.
Saute onion and pepper in drippings.
Remove to paper towel with slotted spoon. Add water, tomato puree and eggplant to skillet.
Cook, covered, 10 minutes.
Add sauteed items to eggplant mixture.
Toss together.
(Mix bread crumbs, bacon,
crumbled and grated cheese for topping.
Put eggplant mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Place topping over casserole.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Boil chicken 20 minutes.
Remove from bone and toss out skin. Cut into bite size pieces.
In separate bowl, mix soups, beans and salsa (looks awful).
In greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish arrange 1/2 the tortillas cut into strips evenly.
Add chicken pieces. Add remaining strips evenly.
Pour soup mix on top.
Add grated cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turtle candy
directions: Melt bars and milk in top of double boiler.
Pour over pecans. Drop by teaspoon full onto wax paper.
Chill to set.

title: tonya's cheese potatoes with bacon
directions: Cook potatoes in microwave until they are not quite done. (They are not supposed to be soft.) Mix together onion, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Grease a casserole dish with butter. Mix cheese and potatoes with mayonnaise mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle bacon pieces on top.

title: lime pine ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice. Cool. When gelatin is slightly congealed, whip in sour cream with rotary beater. Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour into an 8 1/2-inch ring mold. Chill until set.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions (omit salt from water).
Put in buttered dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake in 325° oven with pan of water underneath.
Bake 1 hour or until browned.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Cut potatoes into slices.
Layer in pan, then add onions, rice with 1 cup water, peas and carrots.
Cook ground beef first.
Then top with tomato soup.
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hrs. at 350°F.

title: breakfast in a cup
directions: Combine rice, 1/2 cup cheese, chilies, pimentos, milk, eggs, cumin, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Divide the mixture evenly into 12 muffin cups coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until set.
Great for brunch or lunch.
May be placed in a Ziploc bag, taken out as needed and microwaved to warm.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Leave enough water in noodles to melt cheese and butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick wheat soy bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Blend liquid ingredients; pour into the dry and blend well.
Pour into a well oiled loaf pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix broccoli and corn with onion, soup, mayonnaise, cheese and eggs.
Put in greased casserole dish and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: tahitian ice cream cake dessert
directions: Line bottom of an 8-inch square pan with ladyfingers.
Spread with ice cream. Top with pineapple.
Cover with foil. Freeze overnight.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Only partially thaw the lemonade and Cool Whip.
Blend thoroughly the lemonade, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour in pie crust.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Garnish with thin fresh lemon slices dipped in sugar, if desired.
A very rich dessert.

title: meat balls
directions: Heat pasta sauce and add mushrooms; simmer 30 to 35 minutes. Mix all other ingredients and shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; drain.
Add to sauce; simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over cooked pasta.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add cranberry sauce; stir well. Refrigerate while preparing other fruit. Add pineapple, chopped nuts, apples & mandarin oranges. Mix well & refrigerate 4-6 hours.

title: spanish lasagna
directions: Mix raw hamburger, beans and spices.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, place four uncooked noodles.
Spread half the beef/bean mixture.
Repeat with remaining noodles and mixture two more times; ending with noodles on top.
Combine water and Picante sauce.
Pour over all the layers.
Cover tightly with foil and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Combine sour cream, onions and olives.
Spread this mixture on layers and top with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients for 20 seconds at high speed.
Pour into a 10-inch pie pan, sprayed with Pam; bake 1 hour at 350° or until knife comes out clean.
Crust will form at bottom, custard in the center and coconut to the top.

title: fudge pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add the egg yolks.
Beat. Add the chocolate.
Add to the mixture the flour and vanilla.
Beat the egg whites with the salt until stiff and fold into flour mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: spam casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam Ease.
Mix all ingredients (top with cheese).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mix
yeast
with
warm	water.	Set aside.
With mixer, beat Crisco
and
boiling
water.
Add
sugar.
Add eggs;
mix well. Add yeast
mixture	and mix well.
Then add flour.	Mix all this together and cover.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Roll out 1/4-inch thick;
dip in melted butter.
Fold over and bake at 450° until brown.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, cocoa and 1 cup water; bring to boil.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat; in large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add cocoa mixture.
Mix until blended; pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place sliced cucumbers in a bowl of water and add 1 teaspoon salt.
Chill for 2 hours.
Rinse off all salt water and add 1/2 cup of vinegar and 2 cups of water to cucumbers.
Add onion, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir and chill for 2 to 4 hours.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a well-floured surface and knead 15 to 20 times.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° on lightly greased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 1/2 dozen.

title: fall apple dip
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and fold in peanuts.
Dip sliced apples into mixture.

title: *dutch apple pie
directions: Pare, halve and core apples; slice 4.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon; sprinkle half over sliced apples.
Arrange remaining apple halves, cut side down, on top of sliced apples.
Sprinkle on remaining sugar mixture.
Pour cream in slowly near the center. Dot with butter.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 1 hour or until apples are tender.
Juice thickens as pie cools.
Remove from oven and press apple halves lightly in juice with a fork.
Serve warm or cold.

title: monster cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, peanut butter and syrup in very large bowl.
Cream until sugars are dissolved.
Scrape bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Combine soda and oatmeal and add and mix well.
Stir in chocolate.
Drop on cookie sheet using a big tablespoon for each.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let cool slightly before removing from sheet.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except pecans.
Then add pecans.
Bake in 2 unbaked pie shells at 350° to 375° for about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: aunt monna's potatoes
directions: Mix the ingredients and put into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: slow-cooked scalloped chicken
directions: Mix bread cubes, eggs, celery, onions, salt, pepper, sage, baking powder, broth and milk in large bowl. Pour a layer of bread mixture in bottom of crock-pot sprayed with cooking oil. Place a layer of chicken, then the rest of the bread mixture with the rest of the chicken on top. Put can of mushroom soup over the chicken and drizzle with melted butter. Cook on high for 4 to 4 1/2 hours (low for 6 to 7 hours).

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Make crust from rolls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate chip dessert
directions: Dip cookies in a small amount of milk.
Place a layer of cookies in a square or oblong pan. Cover with layer of Cool Whip. Repeat as necessary. Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Cut in squares and serve.

title: erma davis' fruit punch
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O according to directions on package and add sugar
and	dissolve.
Add	pineapple,
orange
and lemon juices. Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: munch bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a full boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Pour mixture over corn flakes, mixing well.
Pat in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit ice
directions: Make a syrup of sugar and water by boiling together for 3 minutes.
Squeeze lemons and oranges.
Add to water and sugar. Mash bananas and fold in.
Freeze.
When lightly frozen, take out and beat with a mixer.
Refreeze.

title: linguine with chicken sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes; cover with hot water.
Soak until needed.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and set aside.
In nonstick skillet, cook onion in olive oil until lightly browned, then toss in garlic and chicken from skillet.
Then add flour and broth,
Heat, stirring, until bubbly.
Drain tomatoes and add them along with parsley and basil to mixture in skillet.
Return chicken to pan and cook on low heat for another 10 minutes.
Serve over linguine; top with grated cheese.
Serves 6.

title: cheese straws
directions: Leave butter out to room temperature.
Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients well.
Push through cookie press with the star disk onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, oleo and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Add the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of dough around a kiss.
Keep hands sprayed lightly with Pam to keep from sticking.
Knead dough chilled.
Place dough covered kisses on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: green beans and cabbage
directions: Fry bacon and dice.
Add chopped onion and cabbage; saute 5 minutes.
Add beans and 1/2 cup liquid from them.
Steam 15 minutes.
Add sugar and vinegar; toss and serve hot.

title: oriental corn soup
directions: Pour chicken broth into Dutch oven.
Add pepper, garlic and sesame seed oil.
Bring to a boil.
Microwave or cook peas and carrots.
Mix egg yolks and egg whites in a small bowl and whip slightly by hand.
Remove boiling broth from heat.
While stirring broth, slowly pour in eggs.
Return to medium heat.
Add corn and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to soup.

title: frozen sliced cucumbers
directions: Mix first four ingredients and add to vegetables.
Bag and freeze.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix sweet pickle relish with Miracle Whip salad dressing. Stir together.
Add fresh lemon juice and sugar.
Chill for 1 hour before using.

title: honey curry chicken
directions: Place chicken skin side up, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine honey and remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done, basting occasionally.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy apple dessert
directions: Place sliced apples in a sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Pan should be half full.)
Sprinkle with brown sugar, apple juice concentrate and cinnamon to taste.

title: hungarian stew
directions: Roll stew meat in flour and brown.
Add onion and garlic with carrot.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Serve with noodles.

title: butter bean broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and butter beans.
Do not add salt. Drain water chestnuts and mix with onion soup mix.
Put butter beans and broccoli in casserole dish.
Put mixture of cream of mushroom soup, onion soup and water chestnuts on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: kahlua candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender but firm.
Peel and slice.
Melt butter and sugar in frying pan.
Add sliced potatoes.
Turn until brown on all sides.
Add Kahlua.
Bake in covered dish at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover; ladle syrup over potatoes.
Bake another 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: swinging souffle
directions: Grease casserole.
Decrust bread and cut slices in 3. Cut cheese in thirds, grate.
Layer of bread, etc.
Soak at least 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti dinner
directions: Boil spaghetti.
In large skillet, add diced onion and green pepper.
Add meats; cook until brown in color.
Add all seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomato paste with 2 cups water.
Simmer.
Mix in mushrooms and salt.
Drain water from spaghetti.
Add mixture.
Finally, add sauce.
Let stand 1/2 hour in covered boiler.

title: sauteed tomatoes and zucchini
directions: Peel, core and cut tomatoes into wedges.
Slice zucchini. Over low heat, saute onions and garlic in butter until onions are tender and golden.
Stir in basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add zucchini and cook about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook 5 minutes longer or until zucchini is tender and tomatoes are heated through.
Makes 6 servings.
Can be done in microwave.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and lime juice.
Combine egg yolks and cream cheese.
Beat the two mixtures together until smooth. Pour into graham cracker crust and add meringue.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients; boil until it will form a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat; add 1 jar Marshmallow Creme and 1 cup peanut butter.
Beat well.
Pour into a lightly greased pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: surprise meat loaf
directions: Put the first six things that are listed into a large bowl and stir.
Add the ground beef.
Blend everything together very well. Pour one half of this meat mixture into a large baking pan.
Shape the meat into an oblong patty.
Then make two hollows in the mixture and fit the hard-boiled eggs into them.
Use the rest of the meat mixture to cover the eggs. Shape gently into a loaf.
Lay the bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
When you serve this meat loaf, each slice will have a ring of egg in the middle.

title: pasta shells with broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cook pasta in boiling salted water following package directions.
Drain.
Heat butter and olive oil in large frying pan.
Add broccoli and garlic.
Saute for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pasta, salt and pepper.
Toss well and serve at once.

title: rice balls
directions: Cook rice and put aside in a frying pan.
Mince and brown 1 small onion with chop meat, 1 teaspoon of salt, chopped parsley, 1/2 cup of peas and 1/4 cup of tomato sauce and simmer for 1/2 an hour.
Prepare rice hot.
Mix with Romano cheese thoroughly.
Now make rice balls the size of a baseball.
Make a hole in the center and fill with chop meat.
Mix and close completely.
Next, crack the eggs and separate the yolks from the white.
Take the white and beat it.
Then dip the rice ball and cover with bread crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Mix ingredients; pour over pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: homestyle french dressing
directions: Put all in 1-quart jar.
Shake well each time it is used. Keeps indefinitely.

title: cape cod cranberry breakfast
directions: Lightly brown sausage links and arrange in deep dish pie pan or casserole - like spokes in a wheel.
Mix orange juice and cranberry sauce.
Pour over sausages.
Mix corn muffin batter according to package directions.
Pour batter over cranberry layer.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes until cornbread looks done.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Stir together all ingredients with a spoon. Roll into balls and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: carrie's chili mac
directions: Cook
pinto
beans.
Brown
ground beef, add to beans 1 hour before beans are done.
Add elbow macaroni (cooked).
Add chili mix when beans are done.

title: crock-pot red chili
directions: Layer all ingredients in a crock-pot with meat on the bottom. Turn crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours or high for 4 to 5 hours.

title: super duper biscuits
directions: Mix sifted flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender, 2 knives or fork until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Transfer dough to a floured board or pastry cloth.
Knead lightly about 10 times.
Roll dough 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown as desired.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap chicken in bacon.
Cover bottom of flat baking dish with beef or ham, arranging chicken on top of beef or ham.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: frozen berries 'n cream
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, strawberries and honey. Mix well.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
To serve, let stand at room temperature 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 9 servings.
For individual servings, evenly divide mixture into 9 foil baking cups.

title: bow tie pasta
directions: Toss together pasta and next 8 ingredients; add more dressing as desired. Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Yields 6 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Place in refrigerator overnight or bake then.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together; add to berries.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Add filling; dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Bake in very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Grease a baking pan; put sliced peaches in and add sugar and tapioca.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening. Add 1 well beaten egg; add milk and sugar.
Spread over peaches and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rice porridge
directions: Boil rice in water with salt until partially ready.
Drain water off and put rice in baking dish.
Add milk, raisins, melted margarine, sugar and 1/2 cup water to rice and stir.
Cook in oven at 350°, until top is browned lightly.

title: unbaked holiday roll
directions: Chop or cut into small pieces marshmallows, cherries, nuts, prunes and dates.
Mix marshmallows with cream.
Roll graham crackers into fine crumbs.
Combine chopped dried fruit with crumbs mixed together.
Stir mixture into cream and marshmallows. Mold and wrap in foil; refrigerate for 24 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice mushrooms, julienne onions and green peppers, crush garlic cloves and cut steak into 1/2-inch strips.
Add oil to a hot skillet and brown beef strips.
Add the vegetables, seasonings and wine to skillet and cover.
Let simmer until vegetables are done.
Do not over cook.
To thicken sauce, mix the cornstarch with 1/4 cup of water and add to pan.
Serve over cooked rice. Boneless chicken breast may be substituted for beef.

title: easy egg pie
directions: Put in blender.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Pour in deep pie pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: killer cereal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix oats and chips.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
In food processor, mix sugars; add butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Process until blended.
Add flour mixture.
Process until combined.
Pour over oats and chips until well combined.
Using tablespoon, measure out scoops and place at least 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: haida fried clams(modern)
directions: Shell clams.
Beat eggs into milk.
Dip clams in cornmeal, then into mixture of egg and milk, then into the cornmeal again. Fry in deep, hot fat preheated to 385°, until golden brown.
Allow to drain on paper towel.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening together; then cool until lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water; add 1 teaspoon sugar and stir into first mixture.
Add beaten eggs and stir in 4 cups of flour.
Then beat very thoroughly.
Stir in 4 more cups of flour and mix thoroughly, but it is not necessary to knead.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Shape as desired and put in a warm place until double in bulk (about 2 hours).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 425° oven.
This dough will keep in refrigerator for a week or ten days.

title: chicken-n-dressing
directions: Season and boil chicken in large amount of water to make plenty of chicken broth.
Remove the bones and skin from chicken and return to broth.
Chop up large onion and put in broth.
Add one pan of cornbread at a time.
Will use 1 1/2 to 2 pans of bread.
You don't want it too thick.
Add eggs.
I like mixing it together with my hands.
Put in your sausage seasoning to taste. Add salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cook what you need and the rest freezes very well, if your best friend doesn't get what's left.

title: green bean and tomato salad
directions: Combine beans and 1/4 cup water in a 2 quart microproof casserole.	 Cover	tightly
with
plastic	wrap
turned
back slightly
on 1
side.
Microcook
on
High	4
minutes;
stir. Re-cover and microcook on
High 1 to 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Rinse under cold water.
Drain and chill beans.

title: mexican cornbread 2
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour 1/2 of the batter to edges of pan. Pour in first mixture to 1 inch from sides and top with remaining batter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and vegetable oil well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add alternately milk and flour.
Begin and end with the flour.
Add salt, butter flavorings and coconut flavorings with a spoon.
Add coconut to batter along with a few drops of yellow food coloring.
Bake in a tube pan.
Start cake in a cold oven.
Set temperature at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until brown and tests done.

title: winter vegetable salad
directions: Wash and cut cauliflower into bite sized pieces.
Wash and peel stems from broccoli; cut into small pieces.
Peel and slice carrots thinly or cut into fine matchsticks.
Seed and cut pepper into thin strips.
The carrots and pepper are optional, they add color.
Put in a large bowl.
Pour in salad dressing.
The kind can vary, I like Italian or red-wine vinegar dressing, but I have also used creamy Italian.
That tasted good, but doesn't keep for as long a time. You may need two bottles.
Stir it up and see. You can see it is a very precise recipe!
Keeps well.

title: strawberry rhubarb dumplings
directions: In a
6-quart saucepan, cook rhubarb, strawberries and sugar. Cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes, making sure sauce boils.
Continue boiling.

title: heath bar
directions: Line cookie sheet with crushed graham crackers.
Mix butter and sugar together and boil for 2 minutes.
Then pour over graham crackers.
Bake for 7 minutes (no longer) at 450°.
Sprinkle nuts over top of graham crackers and sugar mixture and bake for 3 minutes longer.
Break into pieces on wax paper.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato paste.
Bring to a boil; add tomato paste.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Fill jars and seal.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt 1 stick butter.
Put it in cup and pour batter into pan. Put peaches on top of batter in pan.
Pour the butter over peaches. Cook slowly until done.
Take out and pour peach juice over the pie.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and dot with butter.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 1/4-inch strips.
Brown in heavy skillet in butter on medium heat.
Add onion soup mix and water, and simmer for 45 minutes to an hour.
Add onions, pepper and worcestershire sauce and simmer until onions and peppers are tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: apple fruit chews
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In colander, rinse apples with hot tap water until wet; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening and sugars.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in cereal and apple until well combined.
Drop by level tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Mix flour and baking powder in gradually.
Add water and vanilla.
Roll into balls.
Roll into sugar.
Press with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add chili powder, salt, oregano and flour.
Mix well.
Add water.
Simmer until thickened. Place layer tortillas (4) in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cheese and 1/3 chopped olives. Repeat twice.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
In buttered casserole dish, break up 8 to 10 slices.
Pour milk mixture over this.
Top with 1 stick of butter; cut in slices.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon and sugar mixed.
Don't use all of it.
Keep rest stored for future.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
(May also add 1/2 can crushed pineapple.)

title: quick brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add peanut butter and cut in well with pastry blender or two knives.
Add milk mixture and beat well. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cheese and blend in cream cheese and seasonings.
Stir in shrimp and add paprika as desired for color.
Serve with potato chips or other dippers.
Yields 1 cup.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by spoonful into boiling chicken broth.
Cover tightly and steam without lifting lid 12 to 15 minutes.
(These are fluffy dumplings.)

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Beat in sugar, salt, corn syrup, flour and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until filling is set in center.

title: amaretto bread pudding
directions: Break up bread into small pieces.
Place in a medium sized bowl and cover with the half and half.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with the butter.
In a small bowl beat eggs, sugar and almond extract.
Stir into bread mixture.
Gently fold almonds into bread mixture.
Spread bread mixture evenly into baking dish.
Set on middle rack of oven and bake 50 minutes until golden.
Remove and let cool.

title: scotch meat pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter.
Blend in soup.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Cover with remaining crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix.
Dip bread into egg mixture.
Turn and soak other side.
Have skillet hot with small amount of butter or margarine.
Brown both sides and serve with maple syrup or jelly.

title: low country shrimp boil
directions: Approximately 1 1/2 hours prior to eating, cut sausage into 1 to 2-inch pieces and place in large pot with onions, celery, Old Bay and beer.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat to simmer and cook for 45 minutes.
Place all of the frozen corn in the pot; adding more water if necessary to cover corn.
Return to a boil and cook 5 more minutes.
Add shrimp all at once and immediately stir into a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and drain.
Serve directly from pot, being careful not to overcook the shrimp.
Serve with a salad and crusty French bread.

title: jack's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into buttered 8x8-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Mix all but chicken, chips and cheese.
Layer Doritos, chicken and soup mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot butter sauce
directions: Melt butter; blend in sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream.
Heat only until hot.
Add vanilla.
Serve warm over sliced cake, white or yellow.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease. Add minced onions and K.C. Masterpiece; cook for 15 minutes on medium heat. Then add bottle of Bull's-Eye. Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally, until almost dry. Serve on bun.

title: dinner salmon omelet
directions: Drain salmon; saute zucchini and onion in 1 tablespoon butter. Remove from skillet.
Beat eggs, water and dill weed.
Add butter as needed in skillet to cook omelet.
When done, spoon on vegetables and salmon.
Fold in half.
Serve with sour cream as topping.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar with 1/2 can coconut. Frost cake with mixture.
Sprinkle rest of coconut flakes on top of cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: vegetable hash soup
directions: Put in large boiler.
Mix together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Boil until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Combine and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery until soft.
Mix soup, milk and Miracle Whip together.
Mix altogether.
Top with crushed cornflakes and 2 tablespoons melted butter that have been mixed together.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix together until yeast is all dissolved.
Add flour enough to make dough.
Roll out after raised once.
Cut with cutter; put in greased pan and let raise before baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Place frozen spinach in strainer to drain and thaw.
When spinach is thawed, mix with other ingredients and refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Prep Time: 35 minutes.
Total time: 2 hours.

title: brownies(never fail)
directions: Bake in 300° oven for 50 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fudgy deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In a medium bowl, blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well with a spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture, beating until well blended. Stir in the chips.
Spread in the greased pan.
Bake 35 to 49 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from the sides of the pan.
Cool well before cutting.
Overbaking ruins the brownies!

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix
beef,
onion
and	bread together.
Form into tiny balls. Brown in skillet in small amount of oil.
Make a sauce of	the catsup, water, brown sugar and wine vinegar.
Add meat balls to sauce.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Baste often.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Slice squash and simmer in salted water until tender. Drain well.
Mix squash with onion. Add salt, pepper and sour cream. Blend well and place in a 1-quart casserole dish. Top with dressing. Dot with butter and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach in microwave according to directions on package. Drain well.
Mix in bowl with stuffing mix, eggs and salt and pepper.
Roll into balls, 1/2 to 3/4-inch.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for about 12 minutes.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: 1. Heat oil and fry onion until transparent.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour or cornstarch.
Beat egg yolks and milk together and add to sugar and flour. Cook until thick, then add vanilla and a little butter.
Alternate pudding, graham crackers and bananas. Top with beaten egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar; brown.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup of boiling water. Set aside.
Mix the flour, oil and lemon extract.
Put in eggs (one at a time). Next, fold in jello. Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar and mayonnaise for dressing in a blender.
Make night before and let soak into macaroni (it will be very runny).
Mix 2 or 3 times to blend dressing into macaroni.
Serves about 20 people.

title: chicken and eggplant stew
directions: Brown chicken in oil or butter with onion and garlic.
In a large pot, add all ingredients and cook until soft, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve alone or over noodles or spaghetti.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes about 35 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together. Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Drain well. Cube cheese.
Chop onion and green pepper fine.
Mix all ingredients with Hellmann's mayonnaise to desired consistency.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes like you were going to make mashed potatoes. Drain well when done; add sour cream, bacon, onion, a little margarine and a little milk.
Stir in salt and pepper to taste; mash well.
A few little lumps won't hurt.
Pour into baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown meat in oil.
Remove meat; reduce heat and saute vegetables until onion is clear.
Add seasonings, Worcestershire sauce, broth and tomato sauce.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add meat and rice and stir.
Cover and cook over medium heat for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Cook an additional 20 minutes over low heat, without stirring.
If chicken broth is from chicken bouillon cubes, reduce salt.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat eggs and add oil and all the rest of the ingredients. Beat 4 minutes.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate to die for
directions: Mix together and press in bottom of spring-form pan.

title: hawaiian chicken pineapple
directions: In a medium skillet, heat oil and brown chicken. Add soup mix blended with reserved juice, water, soy sauce, green pepper and pineapple.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: stone soup
directions: Chicken may be substituted for broth.

title: jelly roll
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar gradually until mixture becomes thick and light colored. Gradually add
flour, then flavoring.
Line a 15 x 10-inch pan with wax paper.
Grease the paper, then pour cake mixture in. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and sugar, then mix with hot Jell-O.
Add fruit, vanilla and 1 cup of blueberries and pineapple juice.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate in covered container. Will keep for weeks.

title: french toast
directions: * If using self-rising flour, omit salt.

title: potato cabbage soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook about 1 hour until done.

title: sausage italiano
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add mushrooms and tomatoes (with juice).
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add sausage, cut into bite size pieces and simmer 10 minutes more.
Add cooked pasta.
Mix and serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut up the butter in a bowl and add sugar; cream together until fluffy.
Add peanut butter, flour and egg; beat until dough is smooth.
Put teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Put them on a wire rack to cool, using a spatula.

title: new mexico spoon bread("the best from new mexico kitchens" cookbook)
directions: Mix all ingredients except chile and cheese.
Pour half the batter in greased 9 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle with half the cheese and chile.
Add remaining batter and top with cheese and chile. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: In a large, deep bowl, alternate layers of first 7 ingredients, beginning and ending with lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise on top, sealing all edges.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover bowl tightly with Saran Wrap.
Chill several hours or overnight. Immediately before serving, toss well.

title: ground beef casserole(made in layers)
directions: Spread meat in bottom of dish.
Spread potatoes on top of meat. Slice carrots on potatoes.
Slice onion on top of mixture. Spread soup on top of casserole.
Cover in foil.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion, crumbs, egg, 2 tablespoons ketchup, milk and seasonings.
Mold in round, flat loaf in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 2 tablespoons of ketchup.
Cover with plastic wrap loosely; cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand after cooked for 10 minutes to firm (temperature High).

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add ground beef cooking lightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients and 2 cans of water.
Cook covered 45 minutes.

title: sweet tarts
directions: Place vanilla wafers in bottom of cupcake paper.
Combine cream cheese (room temperature), eggs and vanilla.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool, and then add Comstock cherry pie filling on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornmeal. Add eggs, margarine, buttermilk and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops in tomato sauce
directions: Brown pork chops in frypan with chopped onion and olive oil until brown.
Pour in crushed tomatoes and tomato paste.
Sprinkle a little oregano to season, or a little garlic salt if you like. Turn burner on simmer or low heat and leave for 2 to 3 hours.
The pork chops will fall off the bone.

title: sandy's cheese green beans
directions: Open and drain green beans. Place in saucepan. Add butter or margarine. Heat on medium until beans are hot. Remove from heat. Add sliced or cubed Velveeta cheese and cover. Let sit, covered, for about 5 minutes, until cheese is melted. Stir and serve.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and powdered sugar.
Press firmly in long cake pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and Pet milk. Pour over crumb mixture.
Spread cherry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, keep refrigerated.

title: goulash
directions: Add macaroni about 10 minutes before Goulash is done.
Salt and pepper.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator for several hours.
This keeps well as long as the tomatoes are fresh.
This makes a large salad (3 quarts).
Do not substitute another spice for salad seasoning. Do not use a salad seasoning with cheese as it gives the salad a strong taste.

title: zucchini-spinach casserole
directions: Place grated zucchini in colander, sprinkle with salt and let stand about 45 minutes.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet.
Add onion.
Cook about 4 minutes or until onion is translucent.
Place zucchini between several layers of paper towels and squeeze out as much liquid as possible.
Add drained zucchini to skillet.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add spinach, paprika and pepper to skillet.
Stir well.
Cook 4 minutes.
Remove skillet from heat.
Stir in Swiss cheese until melted.
Stir in sour cream.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dip in egg, then coat with flour.
Set aside.

title: frito chili cheese pie
