directions: In a greased baking bowl, put a layer of Frito chips, add layer of chili, then cheese.
Repeat process until you get to the top of the bowl, top with cheese and bake at 375 degrees until cheese is melted.
Children love this.

title: scrambled egg and tuna sandwich
directions: In a non-stick skillet, heat oil and then break eggs into oil. Add tuna and scramble together.
When done, remove from heat. Stir in desired amount of Miracle Whip.
Spread on sandwich bread. Serve while warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chops with apples and stuffing
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chop in oil over medium-high heat. Meanwhile, prepare stuffing according to package directions. Spread pie filling into a greased baking dish.
Place the pork chops on top; spoon stuffing over chops, cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover bake 10 minutes longer or until a meat thermometer reads 160 degrees.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake 9-inch pie crust for 5 to 7 minutes or until very lightly golden. Remove and let cool.
Reduce oven to 325°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients and blend.
Separate into 5 bar shapes; wrap in wax paper and put in icebox.
Slice 1/4 inch thick for cookies and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut peaches and pears in chunks.
Drain all fruits.
Cook pudding mix with 2 cups fruit juice; cool.
Add bananas just before serving, if desired.

title: cheese pie(double pan; 13 x 9 x 2-inches)
directions: Hand mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients. When it comes to a boil, spread and push into pan.

title: fresh zucchini pickles
directions: Wash and trim squash; cut into serving size spears.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup salt and cover with ice water.
Let stand 2 hours. Drain, rinse and drain again.
Slice onion and garlic.
Layer squash, onion, garlic and dill in jars.

title: frozen daiquiri slush
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and freeze.
Serve with 50/50, white soda or plain.

title: baked ham with pineapple glaze
directions: Place ham on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 325° until a meat thermometer registers 140°, 15 to 18 minutes per pound for a whole ham, 18 to 24 minutes per pound for a half ham. Combine preserves and juice; mix well.
Stir in nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves.
Spoon glaze over ham during last 30 minutes of baking.
Serve remaining as a sauce with sliced ham.
Garnish ham slices with pineapple and maraschino cherries.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix well.
Make at least the night before for flavors to blend.

title: macaroni and cheese for two
directions: Boil 3/4 cup small elbow macaroni for 5 minutes in water salted with 1 teaspoon salt. Melt margarine in a saucepan. Add flour and mix with the margarine. Add milk.
Add 3/4 cup grated cheese; bring to a boil.

Add pepper. Add salt. Add dried minced onion. Put drained macaroni in a greased casserole. Pour sauce over it. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated sharp cheese. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. For drier macaroni and cheese, bake another 5 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and 1 stick melted butter and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat sugar, vanilla and other stick of melted butter together for 10 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and continue to beat until creamy.
Spread on crumb layer.

title: mouser's yum squash pie
directions: Halve the squash and scoop out seeds and pulp.
Cut squash into 1-inch cubes and steam until tender (about 15 minutes).
Let cool a bit.
Use a spoon to scrape flesh off peel.
Puree squash in a food processor until smooth.
Place 1 3/4 cup pureed squash in a food processor bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into crust and bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn heat down to 350° and bake another 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: marshmallow ice cream
directions: Pour condensed milk into boiler.
Add marshmallows. Stir constantly on low heat.
Fold in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Continue to stir on low heat until all ingredients are melted. Pour in freezer and add whole milk.

title: hand freezer ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 gallon freezer can.
Add 8 parts ice to 1 part salt.
Turn freezer until hard, about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind squash, onions, green peppers and red peppers coarsely and add canning salt.
Place in large bowl.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Next day, drain and rinse in cold water, then add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil for 20 to 30 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of melted butter. Form into a 9 x 13 pie pan. Mix next 4 ingredients. Pour on top of cracker crust. Let set in refrigerator until jelled. Layer with pineapple, bananas, nuts, cherries and whipped topping. Chill for at least 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: mocha coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store covered in refrigerator for 1 week to blend.
Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons with boiling water. Makes a great gift.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs, 1 box pudding and 7-Up well. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vanilla pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar and mix.
Add eggs one at a time, alternating with flour. Add vanilla.
Pour into a well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
"No peeping."

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.
Serve in hollowed out pineapple!

title: man's cookie
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake for 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 3 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice and salt.
Fold dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Grease, wax paper, grease again and flour a jelly roll pan.
Spread mixture on pan. Sprinkle top with walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll in towel and let cool.

title: holiday ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve first package of gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and pineapple.
Pour into large mold which has been buttered.
Chill until firm.
Mix cream cheese with cream. Dissolve gelatin in water. Combine with cheese mixture.
Pour over first layer in mold.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup hot water. Add 1/2 cup cold water and pears.
Pour over cheese layer in mold. Chill until firm, then unmold.

title: sausage puffs appetizer
directions: Mix cheese and Bisquick.
Work in sausage.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Can freeze.
Makes 100 balls.

title: ladies' punch(rich and creamy)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Set in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients in large bowl.
Melt margarine with water and oil in small saucepan over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla; blend thoroughly.

title: chip dip
directions: *You may want to cut up your own from the freezer case, it's cheaper.

title: linguine with broccoli, sun dried tomatoes and cheese
directions: Cook the broccoli in boiling salted water for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour cooking liquid into 6-quart pot.
Rinse, drain and coarsely chop the broccoli; set aside.
Add water to the reserved broccoli cooking liquid to equal 4 quarts, bring to a boil and add the linguine and cook al dente.
Drain the linguine, transfer to a heated bowl and toss it with 1 tablespoon of the olive oil.
Set aside.
In a large, heavy frypan heat the remaining 4 tablespoons of olive oil over medium heat.
Add the minced garlic and saute it for no more than a minute.
Add the broccoli, salt and pepper and saute about 2 more minutes.
Add this mixture to the linguine and toss with the sun dried tomatoes, cheese and basil.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
While this dish serves four, it is easily doubled.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Melt 1 stick butter or margarine; let cool.
Fill a 9-inch pie plate with apples; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, the flour and beaten egg to the cooled butter or margarine; mix well.
Spread over apples; bake at 350° until golden brown (about 40 to 45 minutes).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together thoroughly.
Add zucchini. Sift together next 8 ingredients.
May add raisins and nuts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tipple chocolate pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, milk and butter in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes, stirring a couple of times.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Pour into chocolate cracker crust shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours, then top with whipped cream and grated chocolate or dust with chocolate drink powder.
Great for choco-a-haulics!!!

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Put ham hock, water, onion, salt, celery, parsley, tomato sauce (or solid pack tomatoes) and green onion in a large pot and cook for about 1 hour.
Add Portuguese sausage and cook for 15 minutes. Add beans and carrots and cook for another 15 minutes.
Add cabbage, potatoes and watercress and cook for 15 minutes.
Do not overcook the soup.
Makes about 15 (1-cup) servings.

title: pineapple pie 2
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese. Add drained pineapple. Combine cool whip until well blended. Fold in pie shell. Chill.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Layer salmon, cheese and croutons in 8 x 8-inch Pyrex casserole.
Beat eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard together; add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until set.
Serves 6.

title: homemade noodles with roast beef
directions: Mix with fork by hand the flour into eggs.
Add salt; mix in milk to form ball.
Roll out on floured cloth.
Let dry 4 hours. Cut into 3-inch strips.
Let dry 1 hour; cut into 1/4-inch noodles.
Add to 2 quarts broth.
Cook until tender.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Beat on high until mixed.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick. Cool.
Slice bananas and lay on top of cake.
Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and dry pudding.
Beat by hand until mixed.
Spread on cake.
Top with cherries and nuts, then drizzle chocolate syrup on top.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before cutting.

title: ambrosia, fantastic
directions: Toss bananas in orange juice; drain and reserve juice.
Layer orange sections, bananas and strawberries in a serving bowl; cover and chill.
Combine salad dressing or mayonnaise, Sugar Twin and reserved orange juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon mixture over fruit and sprinkle with coconut.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: meatballs(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Cook meatballs in 1/4 cup shortening. Remove and drain. Heat barbecue sauces and preserves until melted. Stir constantly. Add meatballs until coated. Simmer 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: chocolate homemade ice cream
directions: Mix vanilla, chocolate syrup, Carnation milk, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add quart of chocolate milk; pour into ice cream container, adding milk to fill.
Freeze per ice cream freezer instructions.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and pour into a 2-quart ice cream freezer.
Churn until done.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put margarine in saucepan.
Put pan on burner.
Turn butter to low.
Heat until the margarine is melted. Remove from burner.
With pastry brush, brush each side of bread slices with margarine.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Cut cheese slices in half.
Tear off a 20-inch long piece of foil.
Put the loaf back together on the foil.
Place cheese slices between the bread slices.
Wrap the foil around the loaf.
Put the loaf in oven.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles; add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with noodles and bake at 400° until bubbly (about 20 minutes).
Double recipe for 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: old-time popcorn balls
directions: Remove all unpopped kernels from popped corn.
Put popcorn in a large roasting pan; keep warm in a 300° oven.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar. Add cooking oil and sifted dry ingredients, water and nuts.
Beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in bundt pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced cranberry ring
directions: Dissolve jello and all seasonings in water.
Add sauce and rind.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in orange and apple.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold and garnish.

title: jello-banana split snack
directions: Just top the pudding snack with Cool Whip, chocolate syrup and a cherry.
Add a sprinkle of chopped nuts.
Your bunch will go bananas!

title: chilaghetti
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery until done.
Cook spaghetti as per box; rinse with cold water.
Add spaghetti, beans and juices, salt and pepper to ground beef mixture.
Pour into casserole and microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese if desired.
Serve with garlic toast.
Serves 6.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container.
Store in a covered container.
Yields 36 servings.

title: favorite "party cake" recipe
directions: Cook cake.
Cool.
Mix pudding.
Drain pineapple.
Mix together the cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add pudding.
Ice cake. Add pineapple, coconut, nuts and cherries as desired.
(This cake can be made ahead and frozen.)
Double recipe for larger sized cake.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Pour combined barbecue sauce and Italian dressing over chicken.
Cover and marinate 1 hour or more.
Drain, reserving marinade.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar; slowly stir in milk and shortening. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture; stir until blended.
Dough may be chilled until easy to handle.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat until brown on other side; drain well before removing.
Place on paper towels and roll in sugar.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: Mix ground beef, spinach, cottage cheese, garlic, lemon juice, cheeses, egg and seasonings well with hands.
Cook shells and keep in cold water until ready to use.
Then stuff them with mixture; arrange in baking dish, overlapping them.
Spoon tomato sauce on them and grate Mozzarella over top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350° uncovered until cheese is brown.

title: sunday fruit bowl
directions: In a very large bowl, empty peaches and pineapple with juices. Add all other fruits and sugar; stir well.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: west texas corn bread
directions: Preheat oven

on wire rack 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan. Yields 12 servings.

title: chafing dish sauce
directions: Simmer browned meat balls in a mixture of the chili sauce and grape jelly for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blue-ribbon chocolate chip cookies
directions: Pre-heat oven to 300°. In medium bowl combine flour, soda, and salt. Mix well with wire whisk, set aside.

title: quick spinach casserole
directions: Pierce spinach packages.
Thaw in microwave for 2 minutes, using package directions; drain.
Saute onion in 1 teaspoon margarine in skillet or microwave.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add spinach, onion, cheese, soup and thyme; mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle mixture of cereal and 2 tablespoons margarine around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken
until soft and cut into pieces.
Make pie crust with Bisquick and water.
Roll out to thickness of a pie crust. Line
casserole

with crust.	Simmer cleaned and cut vegetables	on

Add
chicken
pieces, parsley flakes and	salt and pepper to taste.
Fill crust with vegetable and
chicken
mixture.
Put
a Bisquick cover on top and bake at 350° until crust is golden brown (approximately 45 minutes).

title: hot crab spread(kathy's favorite!)
directions: Thoroughly combine cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce. Drain and flake crab meat.
Add crab meat to cream cheese, also the onions.
Pour into a greased 8-inch pie plate or small shallow baking dish. Top with almonds.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve warm.
Serve on Wheat Thins or some wheat cracker.

title: no sugar fruit and nut drops
directions: Soak raisins in hot water and drain.
Place fruits and nuts in food processor, then dry ingredients.
Process a few seconds.
Add margarine, egg, vanilla and sweetener.
Process until all is mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
(These burn easily.
I use an insulated sheet.)
Bake at 375° for 8 or 10 minutes.
Remove to a paper to cool.
These keep well in refrigerator.

title: trailer slaw
directions: Grind together the cabbage, green and red peppers and onions. Bring vinegar, sugar and seasonings to boil.
Serve over cabbage and other vegetables.
Let sit 24 hours or longer.
This will keep in refrigerator for a while.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Shake biscuit quarters in sugar to coat.
Drop biscuits in a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle layers with nuts.
Combine brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and butter in a saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Turn out on a plate.
Serve warm.

title: coconut-black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, salad oil and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients, add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts, coconut and flavoring. Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Pour hot coconut syrup over hot cake.
Allow cake to remain in pan 4 hours to absorb syrup. Wrap well.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix chocolate pudding according to package directions.
Fold in chocolate chips and coconut.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Soak cauliflower and broccoli in salt water for 3 minutes. Cut in slices.
Use only stalks of broccoli.
Add sliced water chestnuts.
Mix in pimentos.

title: grandma's low-fat candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Pour over Kix cereal and mix gently until cereal is coated with mixture.
Drop in large spoonfuls on waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will also need a big 8-inch flower pot and silk flowers.

title: chicken on egg bread
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until transparent.
Add flour and remaining ingredients and cook until sauce thickens.
Add chopped chicken.
Serve over egg bread.
Use your favorite corn bread recipe or:

title: baby hot browns
directions: Arrange bread slices on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Broil 6-inches from heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and cook, whisking constantly, until smooth. Gradually whisk in milk.
Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add Cheddar cheese, whisking until cheese melts.
Stir in diced turkey and salt.
Top bread evenly with warm cheese-turkey mixture.
Sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese and half of bacon.
Bake at 500° for 2 minutes or until Parmesan is melted.
Top with tomato slices and sprinkle evenly with remaining bacon.
Yield:
24 slices.

title: dilly bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients except flour.
Add 4 1/4 cups flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring with wooden spoon after each addition, until soft dough forms.
Sprinkle work surface with 2 tablespoons remaining flour.
Turn dough out onto floured surface; knead until dough is smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Spray medium bowl with nonstick cooking spray.
Shape dough into ball and place in prepared bowl.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise in warm place about 1 hour, until dough has doubled in size.
Sprinkle work surface with remaining 2 tablespoons flour.
Punch dough down and turn out onto floured surface; knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Transfer back to mixing bowl (spray with nonstick cooking spray again, if necessary); cover and let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.

title: stewed corn
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet; let get hot.
Add corn and stir to coat each grain.
Then add water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook until just tender.
Before serving, sprinkle with black pepper.
This is good with sliced tomatoes and biscuits.

title: liptauer dip
directions: Beat first 7
ingredients until smooth and well blended. Stir in onions.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Use 1 lb. rye (round) scooped out and 1 regular loaf cubed for dipping.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Pour over carrots and refrigerate overnight or 2 days.

title: tot's a tani
directions: Put chocolate in first, then nuts.
I want some pretzels and grapes in and candy last.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; cut in slices and arrange in 9 to 10-inch deep dish pastry-lined pan; heap high.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and sprinkle over apples.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar,	cocoa, milk and butter. Bring to a full boil. Remove
from
heat. Stir in rest of ingredients. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper or greased cookie sheet.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly; add sour milk.
Soak All-Bran in this for 20 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Makes 12 muffins.

title: candy cane punch
directions: Soften ice cream slightly.
Combine with ginger ale, milk and extract.
Stir until well blended.
Add few drops of red food color until it is bright pink.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef.
Sprinkle onion mix over meat; stir in the water.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In salad bowl, combine lettuce, tomato, onion, green pepper, olives and cheese. Spoon on meat; top with corn chips.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Prepare rices (1 cup dry rice - 3 cups cooked).
(One 6 ounce Uncle Ben's rice is what I use.)
Saute in butter, celery, bell pepper, onion, water chestnuts and pimentos.
Mix in soups, half and half, chicken and rice.
Allow mixture to blend well.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add grated cheese, cook and additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with bacon bits sprinkled.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Combine sugar, flour and spices; sprinkle over apples.
Mix gently.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve with breakfast or as accompaniment to pork or chicken dishes.

title: strawberry spritzer
directions: Let strawberries stand at room temperature 20 minutes.
Place 2 of the undrained packages of strawberries in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
In a large punch bowl or pitcher, combine blended strawberries, grape juice and remaining undrained package of strawberries.
Slowly pour in carbonated water.
Stir gently to mix.
Add red food coloring, if desired.
Makes 24 four ounce servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Blend hamburger.
Cut and shred together; add pork.
Mash butter beans and potatoes up fine.
Add corn and garden peas and stir together, adding tomato paste and catsup.
Stir and blend in well.
Add all ingredients and cook slow or on low temperature. Makes a large quantity.

title: finnish bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; set aside.
Mix together 4 cups warm water, honey, salt and whole wheat flour.
Add melted margarine and mix.
Add dissolved yeast.
Add white flour, 1 cup at a time, until it cannot be stirred anymore.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface; knead in enough flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic, approximately 6 to 8 minutes.
Shape into a ball and place in a greased bowl; turn once and cover.
Let rise until double.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour until golden brown.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Add chow mein noodles and peanuts; mix well.
Drop by large spoonfuls onto cookie sheets covered with wax paper.
Put in freezer or refrigerator until set.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make a white sauce by melting margarine and stirring in flour, salt and (pepper, if desired). Gradually add milk. Add Cheddar and Parmesan cheese and stir until cheese is melted. In a greased casserole dish, layer potatoes, raw sliced onion and cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: berry roly-poly
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll out pastry and line a 1 1/2-inch deep 9-inch pie pan, making a high fluted edge.
Partially bake. Lightly beat eggs with a wire whisk; whisk in sugar, salt, milk and vanilla.
Heat half and half just to scalding.
Slowly whisk into egg mixture.
Pour into pastry shell; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in lower third of oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven heat to 350° and continue to bake until a knife inserted slightly off center comes out clean (about 25 more minutes).
Place on a rack and let cool to room temperature.
Serve or refrigerate for up to 24 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brownies without leavening
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Line it with waxed paper.
Sift flour, then measure.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together on waxed paper; set aside.

title: spread for bread
directions: Whip together.
Spread on sliced banana bread.

title: favorite coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 10-inch pie pan.
Be sure to butter pie pan.
Makes its own crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mild chocolate brownies(delicate and delicious)
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Stir in flour (don't dare put more flour than is said).
Add chocolate melted in margarine.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
(Don't overcook one bit or they will be "rocky-hard".)

title: creamy fettuccine
directions: In a large skillet, cook turkey or turkey sausage and onion until meat is browned, stirring to break up meat.
Drain off any fat.
Stir in cream cheese until combined; add mushrooms.
Set aside.

title: martha's  chicken casserole
directions: Layer cooked noodles in greased casserole dish. Put soups on top, mix rest of ingredient together and pour over top. Cover and bake 350 degrees for one hour.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, milk, sugar, salt and cinnamon well.
Dip 8 slices of bread, one at a time, into mixture and cook in hot skillet with butter.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Serve with syrup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cold mashed potato soup
directions: Place the mashed potatoes in a mixing bowl and beat briefly until smooth.
Beat in the mayonnaise; blend thoroughly.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix until completely blended.
You can do the mixing with an electric mixer, set at low.
Serve at room temperature.

title: pizza dip
directions: Line a 10-inch pan with softened cream cheese.
Top with 1/2 bottle chili sauce.
Cover with sausage, onion and pepper.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Then put sliced olives on top.
Cool sausage and drain.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture with the milk.
Clean blueberries, coat with a little flour to prevent settling and gently fold in blueberries.
Spoon into a greased tube pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all together, being sure sugar is dissolved.
Chill in refrigerator.
Good with beans or as an accompaniment to meats.

title: potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise. Scoop out middle, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Cut each shell into quarters. Brush inside with margarine.
Place on large cookie sheet.
Sprinkle seasoning salt over shells. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Spread bacon over skins.
Sprinkle cheese evenly on top.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: quiche
directions: Place ham, cheese and onion on bottom of pie shell.
Beat eggs and blend in rest of ingredients.
Pour over mixture in shell. Bake 15 minutes at 425°; reduce to 300° for 30 minutes to set. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks (one at a time), beating after each.
Sift flour with soda.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in tube pan for 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Wash well with cold water. Add crabmeat (shells removed).
Add tuna and shrimp.
Chop imitation crabmeat into bite size pieces and add to mixture.
Add onion, relish and green pepper.
Stir thoroughly.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and seafood seasoning.
Refrigerate covered.
Add mayonnaise 1/2 to 1 hour prior to serving.
Mix well.
Serve on lettuce on shaped seafood dishes.
Serves 20 people.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients except turkey.
Cook for 10 minutes. Add turkey.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Serve on rolls.
Makes 10 servings with 311 calories per serving.

title: candy's biscuits
directions: Cut in 6 tablespoons butter, enough buttermilk to make moist dough.
Handle as little as possible.
Bake in 375° oven.
Place on top oven shelf 15 minutes.

title: rye pizza
directions: Fry and drain meat.
Season to taste with the seasonings. Melt the cheese into the meat.
Put meat mixture on the slices of bread; place on jelly roll pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: super barbecue
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add the flour to the ground beef and onions; mix well.
In a baking dish, mix the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Can be frozen.
Great with cole slaw.

title: stuffed vidalia onions
directions: Peel onions.
Remove centers, leaving a shell.
Chop 2 tablespoons onion from centers.
Set aside.
Place butter in onions.
Cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Brown onion with ground beef in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add sour cream, cheese and mushrooms.
Fill onion shells.
Cook on Medium-high in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes, until heated throughout.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry shortcake(shared by va bullard, radford, va)
directions: Sift dry ingredients twice and add to butter, egg and milk, combined, to form a dough.
Pat in greased pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° or even 400° until brown (maybe 12 to 15 minutes).
Wash, cap and cut berries in quarters; put in glass bowl and sprinkle with sugar.
Barely warm, very slowly, then crush slightly.
Split the shortcake and spread both cut surfaces with butter.
Put berries between and on top of the cake, spreading them each time on a cut surface.
Cover with whipped cream, sweetened and to which 1/8 to 1/4 teaspoon vanilla has been added.
Garnish with whole selected strawberries.
Bake in 9-inch round cake pan or may be cut with a large biscuit cutter and baked on a cookie sheet.

title: miracle soup
directions: *You may use all or just your favorites (broccoli, tomatoes, cauliflower, zucchini squash, green or red cabbage, green beans or beets).

title: deluxe macaroni 'n' cheese
directions: In a large bowl combine the cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add Cheddar cheese and mix well. Add macaroni and stir until coated.
Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: raspberry applesauce salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O with boiling water, substituting last 3 ingredients for cold water (mentioned on package). Raspberries may be pured in blender. Chill to set. Yield: 10 to 12 servings. Use 9 x 13 dish.

title: fourteen carat cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well. Stir in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost, if desired, or top with Cool Whip.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft; add diced potatoes, water, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add the thawed haddock; simmer until it flakes easily, about 15 to 20 minutes. Add corn and evaporated milk.
Heat through (do not boil) and serve.

title: green onion dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until almost smooth, cover and chill.

title: grandma's basic cream pie filling
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add whatever flavoring you like (coconut, banana, etc.).

title: peach delight
directions: Cook tapioca in 1 quart water until soft.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Combine all ingredients and pour into dish. Chill until firm.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: waffle mix
directions: Have waffle iron heated and ready.
If needed, spray Pam on first.
Mix all together except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold in.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onions, drain; then add Cheddar cheese and set aside.
Heat soup, milk and Velveeta in microwave or in top of double boiler until cheese is melted.
Then add green chilies.
Fill tortilla with meat mixture, roll tightly and place in baking dish.
Pour Velveeta sauce on top.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Bring water to a boil.
Add potatoes, onion, garlic and celery.
Return water to a boil and add bouillon and seasonings.
Cover and simmer over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove 2 cups of potatoes from stock. Set aside.
Blend remaining chowder in blender and return to pot. Reheat over low heat.
Add corn and reserved potatoes.
Simmer, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in a small skillet.
Add green pepper and scallions.
Saute until vegetables turn a bright green, approximately 3 minutes.
Stir into simmering chowder.
Add cream, if desired.
Add extra salt if desired, or salt individually at table.

title: world's best apple pie for bachelor's
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place your pie crust in a well- greased pie pan.
(I use margarine to grease the pan, makes for a better crust.)
Chop apples into small chunks and slices.
Put brown sugar in the bottom of the pie crust.
Place chopped apples in the crust.
Pour sugar and cinnamon mixture over apples.
Place unmelted butter on top of apples.
Place top crust over apples and poke 4 fork holes to vent.
Bake for approximately 55 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until partially done; drain.
Arrange in a greased baking dish.
Place chicken slices on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Have meats ground together two or three times.
Pour milk or coffee on bread crumbs and let stand 10 minutes.
Fry onion in butter and mix with other ingredients.
Shape into small balls and brown in hot shortening or butter.
Remove meatballs when browned. Make a gravy from pan drippings by adding a bouillon cube dissolved in water.
Thicken with flour.
Milk or cream may be added if you wish.
Return meatballs to gravy and simmer until meatballs are hot.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and drain the meat.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pepper and spread onion on top of the meat.
Then cover with the celery soup and Tater Tots.
Mix cheese soup and milk; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bacon.
(Do not drain beans.)
Add the rest of the ingredients and bake at 350° until totally cooked through, about 1 hour.

title: fish and vegetables(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fish and all other ingredients in foil.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Mix with pumpkin mixture.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour mixture into pan and top with nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on a dampened towel, sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll cake and towel together to cool.
Unroll and spread with following mixture.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until well browned.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: In a bowl, mix together crushed wafers and butter. Spread half of mixture in a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
In a heavy saucepan, heat milk and marshmallows, stirring until smooth.
Cool. Add whipped cream. Spread half of this mixture over the cookie mixture.
Spread blueberries over, then spread rest of marshmallow mixture over.
Top with remaining crumbs. Chill and serve.

title: bird of paradise
directions: Cut fryer in desired pieces.
Beat eggs; dip pieces of chicken in eggs.
Roll in Parmesan cheese.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Fry at medium heat until golden brown.
Garnish platter with lemon slices and parsley sprigs.

title: orange freeze pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in orange juice.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, blending until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in oranges.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until firm, about 2 hours.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: taffy apples on a stick
directions: Stir until well blended.
Dip apples into syrup, turning until well coated.
Place on oil paper to harden.
They may be rolled in chopped nuts or coconut.
Do this immediately after coating.

title: huevos rancheros
directions: Place bacon drippings in large, cold skillet.
Heat about one minute on high heat.
Lower heat to medium.
Add green peppers and onion and cook three to four minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, salt and both peppers.
Stir all ingredients together. Bring to a boil on high heat.
Lower heat to simmer and add eggs, one at a time, making a nest for each in tomato mixture.
Cover skillet.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes until eggs are set.
Serves 4.

title: chicken cutlets in wine
directions: Combine salt and pepper with bread crumbs.
Dip and coat cutlets into crumbs, then into beaten eggs and back into crumbs. Heat oil over medium flame in 12-inch skillet; saute cutlets on both sides until brown, turning with tongs.
Lift onto paper towels to drain.
In same skillet, saute mushrooms for 5 to 10 minutes; do not overcook.
Arrange cutlets in 9 x 11-inch baking dish.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in the eggs. Stir in cream of tartar, soda, salt and flour. Roll into balls the size of	a
walnut.
Roll
in
the sugar cinnamon mixture. Place 2-inches
apart on ungreased cookie sheet.	Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes about 1/2 hour at room temperature, or about 5 minutes in microwave on Defrost setting.
Mix potatoes, sour cream, cheese and soup in large bowl.
Put in casserole.
Cut margarine in patties and place over top of potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about an hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage slices in skillet.
Mix browned sausage, jelly and barbecue sauce in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pour apple pie filling into square pan.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Pour over apple pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: irresistible butterhorn rolls
directions: In a cup, stir the yeast into water.
In a pot, scald the milk or microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup butter and stir until melted.
In a large mixing bowl, blend eggs with sugar gradually.
Add milk and butter mixture.
Add dissolved yeast and stir in 2 to 3 cups flour.
Blend in salt.
Add additional flour to handle dough, placing it on floured surface.
Knead for 5 minutes until smooth.
Shape dough into ball, place in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth; let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down, divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll each part into a large circle. Brush dough with softened butter; cut into pie slices and roll up each slice from widest end.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from baking sheet and cool.
Yields 20 to 25 rolls.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter in a large skillet until tender.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add water and tomato sauce; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in bay leaves, salt and hot sauce.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp; cover and simmer 5 to 8 minutes or until shrimp are done, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend the ingredients, chill and serve.

title: baked parmesan fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Rinse fish and pat dry with paper towels.
Spray a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish with nonstick spray coating; set aside.

title: pecan cheese wafers hors d'oeuvres
directions: Grate cheese.
Cream the butter and blend with cheese. Add salt, pepper and flour.
Mix in pecans thoroughly. Divide dough into two parts and form each half into a long roll about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
The rolls may be frozen for later use.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Place sugar, brown sugar and Karo syrup in saucepan and bring to boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend in well and pour over cereal.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper to set.
Yields 3 dozen.
Very good!

title: cavatini
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain grease.
Add sauce and pepperoni. Cook pasta as directed; drain.
Layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan like lasagna.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cheese is melted.
More cheese can be used, if desired.
Add mushrooms, green peppers or olives for a different taste.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from fruits and bring to a boil.
Pour gelatin in and dissolve.
Cool and add Coke and other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to gel.

title: lemon whippersnappers
directions: Grease cookie sheets. Combine dry cake mix, Cool Whip and egg in a bowl.
Stir until well mixed. Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar. Roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light golden brown. Cool. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pork tenderloin with mustard sauce
directions: Mix soy sauce, bourbon (if desired), and brown sugar and marinate pork several hours, turning occasionally.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and milk together well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Add mashed bananas.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing with spoon.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13 pan. Mix together (by hand) the jar of topping and can of milk. While the cake is still warm, poke holes in cake with the end of a wooden spoon and pour the topping and milk mixture over the cake. Let cool. Put Cool Whip and chopped candy bars on top.

title: oatmeal, coconut and rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream the white sugar, brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and baking powder.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Add oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Cook at 300° for 15 minutes.
Will be very light brown.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Stir-fry first 4 ingredients together until lightly browned and spread on a paper towel.
Mix together remaining ingredients and serve or chill and serve.

title: pickled corn
directions: Shuck, silk and wash ears of fresh corn. Corn may be pickled on the cob or cut from the cob. Boil corn, either whole or cut, for about 10 minutes. Rinse with cold water and pack in a crock. Cover corn with a solution of 1/2 cup salt to a gallon of water or if you are pickling whole ears, sprinkle each layer with salt and then add cold water. Cover with a plate and weight down with a heavy rock. Allow to stand for about 2 weeks in a dark cool place. As the corn pickles, a scum will form; you will need to skim this off periodically. Pickled corn can be eaten as corn-on-the-cob or cut off and fried. No need to can as it can be eaten from the crock.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; spinach should be chopped and cooked. Chill for 1 hour.
Serve in hollowed out round loaf of French bread.
Use hollowed out pieces to make bread cubes for dipping.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding and Cool Whip, then add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill several hours, decorate with cherries, if desired.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients with milk; mixture will be thick.
Add onion and egg; beat.
Refrigerate batter all day.
Drop batter from a small spoon into deep fat.
Cook over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: grandma niel's pretzel salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Set aside.
Place pretzels and margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Spread Cool Whip on top and cool.
Dissolve jello in boiling pineapple juice or water. Stir in frozen strawberries and allow to thicken almost to jelled point (it jells real fast).
Spread over Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oil, oleo or butter flavor Crisco and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt, oats, corn flakes and pecans.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 6 minutes.

title: chris' choco cookies
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar together.
Add one egg at a time; mix.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and baking powder.
Chill overnight or several hours.
Makes 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 350°.

title: raspberry or orange punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Blend in soft drink and milk; alternating the two to decrease fizz.
Ready to serve.

title: shrimp and asparagus casserole
directions: Stir together gradually the flour and cream.
Cook until thick. Stir in vinegar and 1/4 cup cream or chicken broth and season with salt and pepper.
Stir in slightly beaten egg yolk, 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese and shrimp.
Put in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole layers of 1/2 shrimp sauce and 1/2 asparagus; repeat.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grit souffle
directions: Cook grits with milk as directed to make 4 cups.
Stir garlic, cheese and butter into the hot grits.
Stirring constantly, add eggs. Pour into baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 375° until brown on top. Great with steak and as a potato substitute.

title: marinated coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper, onion and sugar in a large bowl. Stir well.
Combine Italian dressing, mustard and celery seed in a small pan.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.

title: icing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Spread on cake.

title: grandma le blanc's texas pecan cake
directions: Dissolve
soda
in
wine
or
bourbon.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add
a
little
flour, wine-soda mixture and lemon extract. Add half of the flour, mix well.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time. Beat
egg
whites
until
stiff.
Add to batter, along with rest of flour.
Add fruits and pecans.
Bake in a tube pan which has been
lined
with
wax paper.
Bake 4 hours at 250°. After cake has cooled, wrap in cheesecloth that has been soaked in bourbon. Store
in refrigerator for at least 2 weeks before serving.

title: gold pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops (use shortening if necessary); pour off fat.
Stir in soup, water, carrots, onion and sage.
Cover; cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Add green pepper; cook 15 minutes more or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: one day sweet pickles
directions: Mix salt in well with pickles and onions.
Let stand 2 hours. Drain and squeeze out salt water.
In a large bowl, add sugar, water, vinegar and celery seed.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add pickles and onions.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 year.

title: pull apart cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters; place in angel food cake pan. Boil 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup brown sugar, 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Let cheese soften. Add grated cheese.
Add bell pepper and pineapple.
Mix all together well.
Form 2 balls.
Roll in nuts. Store in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: plantation coffee punch
directions: Combine hot brewed coffee and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cover and chill.
Combine chilled coffee mixture, ice cream, milk and vanilla in a punch bowl.
Stir gently until ice cream melts.
Top with dollops of whip cream.
Sprinkle with shaved chocolate.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: mission coleslaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, orange pieces, salt, pepper and raisins.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard together and blend through the salad.
Chill and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana french toast
directions: Heat skillet to medium heat.
In shallow bowl, mix egg, egg whites, honey, cinnamon, milk and banana.
Spray vegetable spray on skillet.
Dip both sides of bread in mixture.
Cook on skillet about 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Makes 5 (2 slice) servings.

title: bob's irish soda bread
directions: Sift all ingredients together.
Cut in butter.
Add raisins, then add buttermilk and beaten eggs. Pour batter into two greased bread pans (7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch).
Let stand, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, or until done.
(Reduce baking time if larger pans are used.)

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil pepperoni for 5 minutes, covered with water to remove excess fat; drain.
Pour margarine into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Put in drained spaghetti.
Cover with tomato sauce, 1/2 pepperoni, 1/2 Mozzarella and all mushrooms and onion.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Add Swiss cheese, rest of pepperoni and Mozzarella. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix water and Jell-O.
Let set until starting to thicken.
Add applesauce.

title: spritz cookies(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, vanilla flavoring and flour. Mix well.
Use cookie shooter or roll out and cut.
Place on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: kangaroo pockets
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss together eggs, lettuce, Swiss cheese and tomato.
Add salad dressing and toss.
Slit open pita bread rounds on one edge.
Fill each with portion of egg mixture.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order in a salad bowl.
(Spread mayonnaise layer evenly.)
Toss just before serving.
May be made 3 days ahead.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and flake it in a large mixing bowl.
Beat an extra large egg and add to bowl with a can of undiluted cream of celery soup.
Mix in well 1/2 cup each of chopped onion and Miracle Whip.
Add lemon juice, stuffing and salt.
Lightly grease a loaf pan, pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easter candy
directions: Cream together 3/4 pound butter and 1/2 pound sugar.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add 1 pound sugar, coconut or peanut butter.
Beat well.
Shape into balls or egg shapes.
Put in a cool place on a sheet of wax paper overnight. Coat with melted chocolate.

title: red cabbage with pears
directions: Rub the garlic round the sides of a 6-pint casserole.
Spoon half of the cabbage into the dish, followed by a layer of pears. Season to taste and repeat the layers.
Pour over the stock and lemon juice. Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until the cabbage is just tender.
Adjust the seasoning and stir gently to mix together before serving.

title: shoepeg corn with green chiles
directions: Stir softened cream cheese and butter together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into 2 quart casserole and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and oleo together; press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Beat eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks of oleo together for approximately 5 to 8 minutes.
Spread over the cracker base.
Slice the 4 bananas and spread over the mixture.
Spread the pineapple over the bananas.
Spread whipped topping over this.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: roast beaver
directions: Boil beaver for 15 minutes in a weak solution of soda (1 teaspoon per quart).
Remove from water, rub with salt and pepper. Cover with onion and bacon slices inside and out.
Roast at 350° about 2 hours or until tender.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown, season, and drain ground meat;
Add refried beans, mixing well.
Remove from heat; add tomatoes.
In a 9x13 inch pan layer ingredients beginning with 1/2 meat mixture, 1/3 cheese and 6 tortillas.
Repeat ending with tortillas.
Spread chili evenly over tortillas.
Then sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is browned.
Serve with sour cream.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and arrange broccoli in a greased 1 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch casserole. Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: baked sauerkraut casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add hot dogs.
Place in casserole and bake at 325° for approximately 2 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt onto waxed paper. Combine eggs and milk in a medium-size bowl; add dry ingredients and beat lightly to mix.
Stir in oil and corn.

title: flounder creole
directions: Saute onions, green pepper
and mushrooms.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cook 3 minutes.	Add fish and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, until fish flakes.
Serve over rice.

title: cinnamon crispus
directions: Fry tortilla shells in skillet of shortening until fluffy and crispy.
Butter shell after frying with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: smoothies
directions: Starting with only 1 cup of the juice, blend all ingredients until very smooth, adding only as much additional juice as necessary to blend.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Do not use salt.
Cool.
Pick off bones.
Save broth.
Melt margarine and stir into stuffing.
Use a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Use 1/3 of crumbs in bottom of dish, next 1/2 of chicken, cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup of broth.
Repeat with 1/3 of crumbs, 1/2 of chicken, cream of chicken soup and one cup of broth.
Top with 1/3 of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baklava
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 5 filo leaves in 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Butter each as it is stacked.
Evenly sprinkle 5 heaping tablespoons
of
nut
mixture.
Place
2 leaves on top, brush with
butter.
Sprinkle 5 tablespoons of mixture.
Repeat 4 times.
Place
remaining
filo on top, buttering every second leaf.
Trim
edges
with
sharp
knife.
Score
top sheets into diamond shapes using
up and down motion.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn off
heat.
Let
cool in oven.
Pour hot syrup over Baklava.

title: lori's celebrated chicken wings
directions: Mix together and spread over fresh chicken wings (drumettes). Bake at 375° for 1 hour until browned.
Line pan with heavy-duty foil or use disposable foil pan.

title: corn dip
directions: Drain mexicorn, add other ingredients & chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cinnamon stars
directions: Sift sugar; whip egg whites until stiff.
Mix with sugar gradually.
Add cinnamon and lemon rind.
Whip constantly. Reserve 1/3 of mixture.
Fold in almonds.
Flour a board lightly. Pat or roll dough to the thickness of 1/3-inch.
If it is sticky, use a little confectioners sugar.
Cut the cakes with a star or other cutter.
Glaze the tops with the reserved mixture.
Bake on ungreased tin in slow oven at 325°.
This recipe requires no flour.

title: ravioli
directions: Cook celery, onions and green peppers in oleo (don't brown). Add meat; brown.
Boil noodles separately in salt water.
Mix everything except cheese in a huge bowl.
Add 1/2 pound of cheese. Put in casserole and sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for an hour.

title: louisiana shrimp gumbo
directions: Make roux of oil and flour.
Cook slowly and stir until golden brown.
Add onions and cook a few minutes.
Add celery and peppers (sweet and hot) and garlic (if using fresh).
Cook a few minutes; add tomatoes and sauces and other spice and seasonings.
Add chicken broth; cook slowly until good soup.
Cook okra a few minutes in hot oil; add to soup when about half done.
When I get this on the stove and cooking slowly, I clean 2 or 3 quarts of shrimp.
Cook 15 or 20 minutes after you put the cleaned shrimp in soup.
Serve over rice.

title: oat raisin cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat margarine until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Mix egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in cereal and raisins. Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes until lightly brown; cool on rack.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 3-quart casserole, toss together green beans, corn kernels, red peppers, soup, sour cream and flour until all ingredients are well tossed and well coated.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and herbs and bake 15 minutes more or until golden brown.

title: old-fashioned bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours or high 5 to 6 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: red cabbage
directions: Remove outer cabbage leaves and core. Cut the cabbage into quarters and then into medium-fine slices as you would for slaw. In a large saucepan, heat the bacon drippings and add the onion and carrots. Saute approximately 3 minutes.
Add the cabbage and toss well so that it's lightly coated with bacon fat.
Mix in consomme, wine, bay leaf, apples, vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir well and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve in individual preheated side dishes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Put all ingredients together; mix well.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: watermelon sherbet
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Spoon small amounts of mixture into blender container and blend until smooth; set aside.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Cook on low and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add to watermelon mixture, stirring well.
Pour into a 1 gallon ice cream freezer container. Freeze according to manufacturers directions.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet fry sausage until cooked.
Remove sausage from the skillet.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of fat and saute onion and green pepper in the fat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine sausage, cheese, flour, green pepper, onion and parsley.
Spread in pie crust.
Mix milk and eggs and pour over meat in shell.
Bake on cookie sheet 35 to 40 minutes or until filling sets.

title: quiche pastry
directions: Sift flour with salt into a bowl.
With a pastry blender or the fingertips, blend the butter into flour.
Stir in egg yolk and water.
Form pastry into a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together cornmeal, baking powder, salt and minced onion. Beat together egg and milk.
Combine with dry ingredients and form into oblong cakes or pones, about 2 x 4 x 3/4-inch.
Fry in deep fat heated to 370° until golden brown.
Drain on paper toweling and serve at once.
Makes about twelve 2 1/2-inch puppies.

title: pea salad
directions: Boil and drain peas. Add sliced eggs and mayonnaise until thick. Add onion, salt and pepper to taste.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Cool with cold water; drain. Combine pepper, tomatoes, onion, salad supreme and Italian dressing.
Mix well.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and form into walnut-sized balls.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Select a young chicken from 1 1/2 to 2 pounds.
Dress and disjoint.
Chill.
Sift flour (about 1 1/2 cups).
Add salt and pepper and roll each piece of chicken in flour mixture.
Place in heavy frying pan with margarine at least 2 inches deep.
Always place larger pieces in first and on hottest part of frying pan. Remember it is important to have margarine very hot when the chicken to keep steam in.
When done and a golden brown, remove and make gravy as follows: Pour from pan all the fat except 2 tablespoons.
Add to this 2 tablespoons flour.
Mix smooth and add 1 cup milk; stir until it boils and is thick and rich.
Add salt and pepper and pour in a separate dish from the chicken.
(If plain gravy is desired, use hot water in place of milk.) Yields 4 servings.

title: fettucine with shrimp and green onion sauce
directions: Saute shrimp in butter for 5 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add broth, milk, Parmesan cheese, wine, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir well.
Combine cornstarch and water, then add to mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, until cheese melts and sauce thickens.
Add shrimp and cook until thoroughly heated.
Toss with cooked noodles.

title: michele's homemade potato leek soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat butter and vegetable oil.
Add onions, leeks and potatoes until lightly brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour in chicken broth and milk. Increase heat and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for approximately 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove and pour through strainer using back of spoon.
Discard pulp.
Return to saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve with warm crusty bread.
Serves 4.

title: cookies from cake mix
directions: Mix all and drop by tablespoon on ungreased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.
Do not overbake.
Good recipe for children.

directions: Brown ground beef with onion in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.

Add tomatoes, water, sauce mix and salt.

Add rice and zucchini.

directions: Cream well shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add peanut butter.
Gradually add dry ingredients. Drop in small amounts on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes at 350°.

directions: Slice bananas in bottom of pie crust.
Cover with pudding (mixed as directed).
Sprinkle pineapple on top of pudding. Cover with Cool Whip.

It can be served cold and can be used with Sweet 'N Low instead of sugar.

directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze to size to fit in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over the frozen punch when serving.

title: creme de menthe squares
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Pour water off potatoes, mash and add milk to mush stage.
Mix sugar, flour and spices together.
Add to potatoes, beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 300°

directions: Brown meats, cut cheese into cubes and melt into meat.

Spread on party rye.
Brown in oven.

Add onions, garlic, chopped pepper, carrots and mushrooms.

Cook 10 minutes.

Spread Cool Whip on top.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

directions: Cook chicken breast.
Bring rice and soups to boil.
Pour over chicken.
Top with dried onions and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

directions: Break the tamales into fourths; line them in a 13 x 9 Pyrex dish. Mix together the Chicken a la King, the evaporated milk and green chilies; pour over tamales. Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes until done.

directions: Cook chicken until tender, remove from bones.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

directions: Throughly drain and squeeze thawed broccoli. Melt butter and fry onions until soft. Add broccoli and stir until most of the moisture is gone. Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and stir until the mixture looks like green and white marble. Pour into Baked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 min, or until top is golden, and filling is set.

directions: Brown ground beef; drain any fat.
Add chili powder, cumin, garlic salt, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cool, then add chili beans, olives, avocado, grated cheese and lettuce (chopped or cut into small pieces).
Chill.
Just before serving, add crumbled Dorito chips and toss with either 1 bottle Kraft Italian dressing or Kraft Catalina dressing.

directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; melt at a low temperature in a saucepan on the stove, stirring constantly.
Once melted, add 1 box Crispix cereal and stir to mix.

directions: Thinly slice potatoes and onion.
In 9-inch pie pan, layer 1/2 the potatoes and 1/2 the onion.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon dried herb (basil, oregano or tarragon).
Drizzle with 1 tablespoon butter.
Repeat the layers.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Uncover, bake 10 to 20 minutes. Can also microwave covered with Saran Wrap.
Do not overcook.

directions: Heat first five ingredients until all melts.
Chill until half set.
Fold in next 3 ingredients and chill further.

directions: Wash and hull berries.
Place in blender.
Add sugar and lemonade concentrate.
Add 3 lemonade cans of water.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into a punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and mix well.
Add block of ice.
Serve chilled.

directions: Cut a thin slice from stem end of peppers.
Remove seeds and ribs.
Precook peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine meat, rice, seasonings and egg.
Mix tomato sauce and gravy; add 1 cup to meat-rice mixture.
Stuff peppers.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce mixture around peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

directions: Blend ham, olives and mustard.
Add hot sauce to taste.
Form in ball on serving dish.
Chill.
Combine cheese and milk.
Frost Ham Ball.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.

directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together sugar, oil , eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking soda and add to first mixture alternately with the evaporated milk, mixing well.
Add Solo poppy seed filling and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Turn batter into greased and floured bread pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool on wire racks.

directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place hash browns in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix other ingredients, except crackers. Spread mixture on top of hash browns and top with crackers.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan; cool. Prepare pudding as directed; refrigerate. Drain pineapple. Slice strawberries. In bottom of large punch bowl, break up 1/2 of cake; cover with 1/2 of pudding. Layer 1 can of pineapple tidbits, 2 sliced bananas and 1 quart sliced strawberries, standing 1 roll of strawberries around edges of bowl. Fill center with remaining quart. Cover with 1 small tub of Cool Whip. Repeat 2nd layer in same order, using 1 large Cool Whip to cover top.

Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, milk and baking powder in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into prepared dish.
Spoon blackberries and juice over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large, shallow dish; toss gently and set aside.

directions: Follow Solomon's prescription in Proverbs 23:14 and you will have a celebrated Sunday cake; besides being a very good cake to eat, it makes a fine conversation piece.

The best cakes are made by the baker who took time to read not only the exact verse, but also the chapter in which the verse was found.
Hope you have good luck with it.

title: chicken pot pie with celery seed pastry
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables.
Remove from heat until ready to pour into pastry.
Prepare Celery Seed Pastry.

directions: Mix butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract together.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda together. Combine jam and sour cream.
Add jam mixture alternately with flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

directions: Note:
Amount of potatoes and carrots will vary depending on the number you are serving!

directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar, oil and vanilla and blend well.
Add zucchini.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to batter.
Turn into pans and bake about 1 or 1 1/4 hours until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool on rack; remove pans.
Wrap and store overnight to develop flavors.
Can be frozen if properly wrapped.
(This batter is on the thin side.)

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs by hand.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shells evenly.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool and enjoy.

title: cheesy onion puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place 1 sheet of puff pastry on a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Spread cheese onion mix on top of pastry.
Top with remaining pastry sheet.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef; drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour in casserole.
Cut biscuits in halves; place cut side down around edge of casserole. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.

directions: Pour boiling water over the first 4 ingredients; let stand 10 minutes and then drain.

directions: A perfect summer meal.
The only thing that's difficult is finding the Korean chickens!!

directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add macaroni.
Toss to coat well.
Add tuna and vegetables.
Toss gently.
Cover.
Refrigerate until serving time (at least 4 hours).
Makes 6 cups or 4 servings.

title: baked cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, sugar and crumbs. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch pan.
In bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon; mix well.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and nuts.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Fold into apple mixture.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: egg nog
directions: Blend well whipping cream and eggs in blender; finish filling blender with milk.
Add rum, food coloring and sugar and blend well.
Chill until ready to serve; put back into blender and fluff.
Pour into glasses and garnish with maraschino cherries and nutmeg.

directions: Prepare and bake cake according to directions.
Meanwhile, combine milk and sugar in a saucepan; cook until hot and add 1 package of coconut.
Punch holes in cake, while it is still hot, and pour mixture over cake.
Let cool and then turn upside-down onto a long board; cover with Cool Whip and top with remaining 2 packages coconut.
Refrigerate.

directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Beat together eggs, cream, salt, nutmeg, pepper and sugar.
Grate cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and mix well. Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add, stirring well. Chill.
Make into balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Can add butterscotch chips or chocolate chips. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

jello
over rhubarb and sprinkle topping over rhubarb and jello.

directions: Saute pecans in margarine until lightly browned.
Drain and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with pecans.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat all ingredients except egg whites.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Butter spring pan and line with graham cracker crumbs mixed with melted butter (approximately 2 dozen crackers).
Save some crumbs for decoration.
Pour in cream cheese/egg mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Set aside to cool (about 1/2 hour).

title: whole green beans with bacon
directions: Wash beans and remove ends.
Leave beans whole.
Cook and stir beans, bacon, water, salt and pepper for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat. Cover.
Cook 25 minutes or until beans are tender.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Mix well.
Place in casserole, tightly covered.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Could use crock-pot.

and

and

and

heat

Serve with a green salad.
