Add the beet juice, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until thick and smooth.
Add beets and cook over low heat for about 20 minutes.
Add the melted butter; mix well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Spoon in squash.
Add vanilla. Alternate dry mixture and milk.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Pare, core and slice apples as if for pie.
Mix in cinnamon and sugar, let stand.
Mix all remaining ingredients in large bowl. Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour in half of the batter, then 1/2 of apple mixture.
Pour on other half of batter and top with rest of apples.
Pour juice from apple mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds oven bag.

title: egg custard pies(makes two 8-inch pies)
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and flour; stir well.
Add milk.
Stir thoroughly!
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Put nutmeg over top.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked corned beef dinner casserole
directions: Place in layers in casserole, pour on soup mixture and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When baked, place sliced olives on top and garnish with parsley.

title: cranberry swirl coffeecake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nutmeg in a mixing bowl; set aside.
Beat margarine or butter in a large mixing bowl until softened.
Add eggs and almond extract. Beat until well combined.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream, beating just until combined.
Spoon half of the batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Spoon half of the cranberry sauce and half of the walnuts over the batter.
Repeat layers with remaining batter, cranberry sauce and walnuts.
Gently cut through the mixture with a knife to swirl.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until the cake tests done.
Cool on a wire rack for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together well with mixer.
In another bowl, mix together pudding, Cool Whip and milk. Combine both mixtures together. Grate up both packages of cookies. Put plastic wrap in bottom of a large flowerpot.
Layer dirt (grated cookies) and filling.
May also add 3 packages of gummy worms. Add plastic flowers on top. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add chopped nuts mixed with flour.
Stir in chocolate and butter mixture after it has cooled. Pour into greased and warmed pan.
Spread mixture in pan and bake in 325° to 375° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cover with foil first half of baking the uncover and bake until turning brown.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers; add to vinegar and sugar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add pectin.
Boil for 1 minute.
Let set 5 minutes.
Put in jars.

title: nanny billingsley's frosting for strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell until brown.
Place whole strawberries in cool pie shell.
Combine sugar, salt, cream of tartar and water; bring to boiling.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
Place egg whites in small bowl of electric mixer.
Pour boiling syrup until spreading consistency.
Add vanilla.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: Puree mushrooms, a small amount at a time, in blender with some of the chicken broth.
Pour into a heavy saucepan.
Add any remaining broth and the heavy cream.
Season to taste with salt and freshly ground nutmeg.
Bring to a boil over low heat; do not cook further.
Serve immediately in heated soup mugs with garnish of parsley.
Serves 6.

title: club soda waffles
directions: Mix all together very lightly. Cook all waffles; do not save leftover batter. It is alright to freeze cooked waffles, then heat in toaster later.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Place grapes on a wire rack (individually or in bunches). Beat egg whites just until frothy.
Using a paint brush, brush the grapes with the egg whites.
Drain.
While grapes are wet with the egg whites, sprinkle with granulated sugar to create a frosted look.
Allow to dry in a cool place.
Do not refrigerate.
Use the same day.

title: peach melba dessert cups
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions using skim milk.
Stir in peaches; spoon mixture into six (6 ounce) dishes. Chill at least 1 hour.
Just before serving arrange 4 cookie quarters in each dish; top each with 1/2 teaspoon preserves.
Makes 6 servings; 151 calories; 399 mg. sodium; 1 gram fat per serving.

title: peach punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar with water in a saucepan on top of the stove; let cool.
Put peaches in a food processor; process for 1/2 minute.
Add your milk and peaches to your Jell-O mixture. Prepare this ahead of time.
Put in freezer; let get really cold. Add ice cream and ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Simmer until hot. Add cooked carrots and heat.

title: baked chocolate pudding
directions: Sift together flour, salt, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa. Add milk, melted butter and vanilla. Mix together and place in a buttered baking dish.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Gently pull off eight leaves from cabbage.
Simmer in 1 inch boiling water, covered, for 5 minutes.
Drain and lay out for filling.
Combine ground beef and pork.
Saute in butter until brown.
Add salt, pepper, onions, garlic and rice.
Fill leaves with mixture, using 1/8 of it for each.
Roll up each, folding ends to center.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place in a greased skillet. Add tomatoes, cover and place in 350° oven.
Cook for about 45 minutes.

title: scotch raisin bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually until fluffy.
Add buttermilk and molasses; mix well. Sift flour. Add salt, baking powder and soda. Add to egg mixture.
Mix well. Add oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour. Freezes well. Serve with cream cheese.

title: baked macaroni, cheese and cauliflower casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in a casserole dish, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine lettuce (wash and drain; same for bag of salad), peeled cucumbers (cut into small pieces), tomatoes (cut into small pieces) and black olives; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: coconut icebox cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, eggs and water.
Bake cake according to mix directions.	Mix 2 cups of milk and 1 cup of sugar to a slow boil.
Poke holes in cake and pour mixture over cake.
Refrigerate overnight.	Top with Cool Whip and coconut.
One cup chopped nuts is optional.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan.
While still warm, spread on cream cheese.
Let set a few minutes, then spread on drained pineapple. Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: "tomato soup"
directions: Cut up tomatoes, celery and onions.
Cook vegetables together until tender.
Run through colander.
Add sugar and salt.
Heat, but not to boiling.
Add oleo and flour; blend well and add to soup.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Put in jars and seal. Pressure 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.
Or use water bath 15 or 20 minutes.
Let cool and remove jars.
Will keep well until all used up.
Very tasty!

title: mexican salad (dip)
directions: Mix taco seasoning and refried beans together.
Season to taste with Tabasco sauce.
Spread the mixture evenly on a platter. Spread the package of sour cream over the bean layer.
Mix the chopped ingredients together (do not drain the chilies or olives) and spread the mixture evenly over the sour cream layer.
Top with a large package of shredded cheese.
Dip and eat with tortilla chips.

title: miss sarah's lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans and drain.
Add onion, pimento, bell pepper and mushroom soup.
Cook until all is tender.
Stir in cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Melt butter and add bread crumbs.
Place on top of bean mixture.
Put into 400° oven for 25 minutes or until top is brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, bell pepper, cream cheese, and 1/2 c. salsa in saucepan on low heat until cream cheese is melted.

title: cherry nut dessert
directions: Whip sugar and cream together until stiff.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all by hand.
Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 6 ounces of butterscotch bits.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: judy's cherry pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Fold in cherries.
Next, fold in pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour into a pie plate which has been lined with vanilla wafers.
Chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Bake at 350° 20 to 30 minutes until bubbles real good.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 10 x 15 inch jelly roll pan or a 9 x 13 inch pan. In large bowl, combine ingredients. By hand, stir until well blended. Pour into prepared pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake in pie shell at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Soak coconut in milk overnight.
Combine other ingredients next day.
Add coconut.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust and bake at 225° until done.

title: sweet sour carrots
directions: Melt butter; add liquid, salt, pepper and cloves.
Cook until thick.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Pour over cooked carrots and bake for 10 minutes.
Take out cloves before serving.

title: squash supreme
directions: Cook squash, carrot and onion together, drain.
Mash squash, add sour cream and soup, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle layer of bread crumbs into a 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spoon mixture over crumbs and then top with crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: roll-ups
directions: Wrap
bacon around
chestnut
slices
and
secure
with toothpick.
Make sauce by mixing the catsup, sugar and vinegar together.
Bake the chestnut
slices
for
30 minutes at 350°. Drain
off excess drippings and pour the sauce over the chestnuts. Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: aunt louise's chicken casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: date roll candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk to form soft ball.
Add dates.
Take from fire.
Add pecans, butter and vanilla.
Beat until holds shape. Wrap in damp cloth.
Slice when chilled.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt broken chocolate in double boiler over 1-inch hot (not boiling) water, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows and walnuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Chill until firm.
Remove candy and cut into squares.
Makes 18 pieces.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in pineapple.
Put in bread mix.
Put into a casserole dish.
Place pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy black forrest cake
directions: Drain cherries reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine reserved juice, cherries, sugar & cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook & stir over low heat until thickened.
Add vanilla & stir.

title: corn flake candy

Pour over the corn flakes. Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: broiled haddock with mushrooms
directions: Cut fillets into serving size pieces.
Melt margarine and brush one tablespoon over fish.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Combine melted chocolate with shortening and blend well.
In another bowl, sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
In another bowl, beat eggs and add sugar gradually, beating until very light.
Add vanilla and chocolate mixture to egg mixture.
Add dry ingredients, spread about 1/2-inch deep in greased paper-lined shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: patterson's best salad dressing ever
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and salad dressing mix as directed on package. Add the Peccorino Romano cheese. Shake well and serve over the salad.

title: whoopie pies with peanut butter frosting
directions: Cream together 1 cup of the butter or margarine and egg. Add 1 cup white sugar, vanilla and hot water. Stir in the flour, cocoa, and baking soda and mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes. Sandwich cookies together with peanut butter frosting.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
In a bowl mix crab cut in chunks, celery, onion, parsley and sliced olives.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly.

title: pineapple glaze
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in undrained pineapple and the lemon juice.
Bring to boiling, stirring, over medium heat.
Boil for one minute.
Mixture will be thickened and translucent.
Stir in food color.
Let cool thoroughly before spreading over top of cooled cheesecake.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Press beef into bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread soup evenly over top of meat.
Arrange Tater Tots over soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: steak parmesan
directions: Dip meat in egg. Roll in mixture of Parmesan cheese and crumbs. Brown steak on both sides until golden.
Place in shallow baking dish.
In skillet, cook onion over low heat until soft. Stir in seasonings and tomato paste. Gradually add hot water, stirring constantly. Cook 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over meat. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese melts through.

title: low-fat banana bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, molasses, oil and egg whites all at once, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in bananas.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: salmon stew
directions: Bring to boil the potatoes and onions; simmer until tender. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour broth from salmon into stew.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition. Stir in vanilla and other flavoring. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool cake in pan for 10 to 15 minutes, then remove from pan and cool completely.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Put cooked rice that has been drained in colander and cold water run through it into bowl.
Add pineapple and some of the juice (not all).
Add whipped cream beaten stiff and cherries. Serve cold with nuts, chopped fine, sprinkled on top if desired.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook
hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, water, chili powder, sugar, catsup and beans.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Put small amount of oil in bottom of 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour mixture into pan.
Top with mixture of cookie crumbs and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
If top starts to brown, cover with foil until done.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in a dishpan in order given.
Drop by ice cream scoop and flatten.
Place about 6 to a cookie sheet. Bake for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Recipe doesn't call for flour.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pound veal cutlets to 1/8-inch thick on cutting board with meat mallet.
In a shallow dish, combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese and mix well.
In another shallow dish, beat egg and water. Dip veal into egg mixture, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
In shallow nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, brown veal.
In a shallow 2-quart baking dish, arrange cutlets and pour sauce over veal.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese and oregano over veal. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: heat and eat barbecue
directions: Mix and heat.
Place on bun.
Top with dill pickle slices.

title: perfect cornbread(every time)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease bread pan or muffin pan lightly. Sift meal and flour, then mix all ingredients together, using enough milk for consistency.
Add about 1 tablespoon cooking oil; mix well.
Bake until golden brown.
Yields 12 muffins or 1 hoecake.
Oven temperatures may vary.

title: slicker dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter; add to dry ingredients.
Roll thin; cut into 1-inch squares or 2-inch long strips.
Drop into hot chicken broth; cook until done.

title: friday fry
directions: In a wok or large frying pan, heat oil.
Beat egg with 2 tablespoons of water until frothy.
Pour into hot pan and let set. Using a spatula, cut egg into strips and scramble.
Add onion. Cook 1 minute.
Add rice and enough soy sauce to turn it brown. Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vegetables and chopped meat.
Stir well until heated through.
Serve.

title: salsa
directions: Chop the tomatoes fine and add all the chopped onion, peppers, diced tomatoes and chilies and seasoning.
Cook over slow burner 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool and eat with chips.
It also makes great taco sauce.
You can add more hot peppers.
I let people add their own if they want it hotter.

title: almond poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together and beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or when pick comes out clean.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease one 9x10 inch tube pan. Cut biscuits into quarters. Mix white sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag. Shake 6 06 8 biscuit pieces into the mixture. Arrange pieces in the bottom of the pan. Continue until all biscuits are coated and placed in a pan. If using nuts, arrange them in among the biscuit pieces as you go along. In a sauce pan over medium heat, melt the margarine with the brown sugar and let boil for one minute. Pour over the biscuits. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes. Let bread cool in pan for 10 minutes and then turn out onto plate. Do not cut. The bread pulls apart.

title: spicy beef hoagies
directions: Hollow out French bread, leaving 1/4-inch side walls.
Mix Sloppy Joe mix and water with browned hamburger together.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Then layer meat, chilies and cheese in bread wells. Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: lemon dill chicken loaves
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter until sizzling.
Stir in salt, dill weed, pepper and garlic.
Add chicken breasts.
Cook over medium-high, turning occasionally, until chicken is browned and fork-tender, 10 to 19 minutes.
In small bowl, stir together remaining ingredients (except rolls, lettuce and tomatoes).
To assemble:
Spread cream cheese mixture over bottom half of roll. Top with lettuce, tomatoes and sauteed chicken breasts.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture over chicken; top with bun.

title: bakeless fruit cake
directions: Mix
thoroughly
all
ingredients, press firmly in tube pan or loaf pans lined with oiled, heavy wax paper.
Let stand overnight in
refrigerator.
Will keep moist if well covered. Serve sliced. May serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges.
Add sugar and nuts and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt chocolate; mix with oil and sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except evaporated milk together. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until potatoes and carrots are done.
Add evaporated milk and simmer, 15 minutes, on low heat.

title: shuck beans
directions: Wash beans; drain and break into pieces.
Take outside and spread on a clean cloth on a piece of tin in a clean place. Beans will dry in 1 to 3 days.
Always bring in at night to keep dew off.
When beans are dry, put in plastic bags and freeze.

title: fresh apple coffee cake
directions: Beat oleo at medium speed, gradually add the 2 cups sugar. Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to the creamed mixture.
Stir in the apples and vanilla.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Combine the 1 1/2 tablespoons of sugar and the cinnamon.
Sprinkle over the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: cauliflower with cheese
directions: Cook
cauliflower in salted water for 12 to 15 minutes. Drain and
place	in
shallow baking dish.
Mix salt, pepper, mayonnaise,
mustard
and
cheese and spread over cauliflower. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and layer between ground Oreos. Refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: baked stuffed clams
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; chop fine.
Add butter and garlic to pan; cook 1 minute.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook until vegetables are soft.
Stir in bacon, clams, bread crumbs, parsley, lemon juice and Tabasco.
Divide stuffing among 24 reserved clam shells.
Bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes with peel and place in baking dish. Saute onion, mushrooms and green pepper in oleo. Mix tomatoes and melted cheese with onion mixture and pour over potatoes. Heat in 325° oven until cheese is bubbly.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter in mixer bowl.
Add egg, salt and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spoon into pie shells. Chill whipped cream until stiff.
Fold in nuts and pineapple. Pour over sugar mixture; chill thoroughly.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Set aside.
Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs. Blend in flour mixture. Add bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured loaf pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: party spaghetti
directions: Saute the onions in 2 tablespoons oil until brown.
Add meat and brown, then carrots, peppers, parsley, mushrooms and tomatoes. Cook slowly for 1 hour and then add garlic, pepper and salt. Cook the spaghetti and add to the meat mixture.
Mix thoroughly and let set overnight.
Heat and serve on a platter or put in heatproof casserole and cover with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 10 or 12.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 2 or more hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with raw cauliflower and broccoli florets, carrot and celery sticks, mushroom caps, cucumber slices and bell pepper strips arranged around a small bowl of dip on a tray.

title: pear-pecan salad
directions: Drain juice from pears and reserve 1 cup of liquid.
Bring the juice to boil on high heat of electric range.
Remove from heat and add lemon flavored gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Place pears and cream cheese in blender container and blend until of creamy consistency.
Stir in gelatin mixture.
Add pecans.
Whip the cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into mold.
Chill.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except pecans and paprika).
Form in a ball; roll in pecans and sprinkle with paprika.

title: angel crisps(yields 4 dozen cookies)
directions: Cream together sugars, butter, shortening, egg and vanilla. Add combined dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip top half in water, then in sugar. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down in center with finger.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, salt, ginger and baking powder. Combine the butter and boiling water. When the butter melts, add the molasses.
Stir into the flour mixture and beat just enough to make a smooth batter.
Put in an 8-inch square pan. Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: raisin bars
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Mix in rest of ingredients; stir well.
Spread evenly in well-greased pan.
Bake quickly. Cut into squares while still hot and roll in powdered sugar.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix following package directions.
Use 1/2 of cake and break into pieces in bottom of punch bowl or large bowl. Pour pineapple over cake.
Pour pudding over pineapple.
Pour strawberries over pudding.
Slice bananas over strawberries. Spread Cool Whip over top.
Cover and let stand overnight.
This recipe if better for a party or large crowd, but can be made smaller by using 1/2 of recipe.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: In slow cooker, combine flour, garlic powder, pepper and paprika.
Trim excess fat from beef.
Cut beef into thin strips. Toss meat in flour mixture in slow cooker.
Add mushroom soup, water and dry soup mix.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on high 3 to 3 1/2 hours or on low for 6 to 7 hours until meat is tender.
Ten minutes before ready to serve, add sliced mushrooms and sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over top of white rice.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all together.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O and mix in; chill.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans;
stir just enough to moisten batter.
Spoon batter into well-greased
and
floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for
60 to 70 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then on rack.

title: chocolate-dipped strawberries
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate over very low heat until chocolate is almost melted.
Remove from heat; stir until smooth.
Or microwave on High 1 minute.
Stir and microwave 30 seconds more. Remove from oven and stir until smooth.
Stir in vegetable oil. Dip half of berry into melted chocolate, letting excess drip back into bowl.
Place on waxed paper covered tray and chill until chocolate is set.
Remove from refrigerator.
Berries can stay at room temperature 12 hours.
Do not chill again or they will weep. Makes 24 to 28.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy gauge saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add to Toll House milk chocolate morsels and Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels; stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla extract.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop ham very fine.
Mix all other ingredients, except crushed pecans, and put into refrigerator until you can form into a ball. Roll in crushed pecans.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Fry in hot skillet, turning once to brown both sides. Enjoy.

title: wood furniture cleaner
directions: Set pan in pail of hot water.
Wash furniture, then wipe with soft cloth.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, applesauce and dry sifted ingredients.
Add raisins.
Bake in loaf pan (lightly greased and floured) at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Drain.
In large pot, melt butter and saute onion and garlic.
Add ham bone, (I find it best to always add extra ham), dried beans and cover with water.
Add bouillon cubes, pepper and Tabasco.
Simmer slowly for approximately 2 hours or until beans are tender.
During last 30 minutes of cooking, add sausage and salt.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Serve over cooked rice with extra Tabasco sauce on side and crusty French bread.
Serves 8.

title: marilyn's sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs and vanilla slightly in large bowl.
Add shortening, butter and sugar and mix thoroughly.

title: shrimp fajitas(original recipe)
directions: Heat pan over high heat.
Add oil and heat 10 seconds.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Remove from pan.
Add onions and scallions to pan and brown quickly.
Remove from pan.
Add red pepper and brown quickly.
Remove from pan.
Add zucchini and brown quickly.
Remove from pan.
Add tomatoes and brown quickly. Put shrimp and all vegetables back in skillet together with jalapeno powder and fajita seasoning.
Mix well and warm through. Serve on warm tortillas and salsa.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Wrap biscuit around cheese, then roll in margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and dice apples.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: halibut-vegetable dinner bake(serves 6)
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen; cut into serving size portions.
Arrange onion in bottom of greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top onion with fish.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on top of fish.
Combine wine, lime juice and seasonings; pour over vegetables.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Contains 230 calories per serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine.
Add eggs and pecans.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and bake in moderately hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookie crumble cheesecake
directions: In a blender, sprinkle gelatin over cold milk.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Add hot milk and process at low speed until dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and process until blended.
Arrange chocolate in the bottom of the graham cracker crust.
Pour in gelatin mixture, sprinkle with crushed cookies.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: bishop cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Use juice from pineapple to mix cake instead of water.
Bake.
Sprinkle top of cake with nuts.
Mix instant pudding according to directions on box.
Fold in drained crushed pineapple.
Spread on cool cake.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread over pineapple mixture. Sprinkle with coconut.
Top with maraschino cherries.

title: jello no bake cheesecake squares
directions: Combine crust mixture with sugar and margarine as directed on package.
Press firmly into bottom of 8 or 9-inch square pan.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Add vanilla and flour mixture; mix.
Chill overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop teaspoon of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar and shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: play dough
directions: Take one large grassy field, one half dozen children (all sizes), one dog and one long narrow strip of brook.
Mix children with the other ingredients and empty them into the field, stirring continually.
Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Pour brook gently over pebbles.
Cover all with a deep blue sky and bake in a hot sun.
When children are well browned, they may be removed.
Will be found ready to cool in the bathtub with lots of soap and warm water.

title: buttermilk flapjacks
directions: Beat eggs; beat in remaining ingredients.
Fry at 375°.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Spread roll dough on large cookie sheet, pinching seams together to make one large sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown and crisp.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix until smooth.
Fold in chopped onion. Spread on cooled roll.
Sprinkle evenly with chopped vegetables and cut into small squares.
Chill and serve.

title: quick pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening in mixing bowl.
Put a lid on it and shake until it looks like corn meal.
Add ice water and vinegar; shake until it forms a ball.
Roll out and place in a pie plate.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: grandma's old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Sift together first 7 ingredients. Stir in melted shortening, molasses, egg and sour milk. Beat in hot water. Bake until cake will spring back when touched.

title: papaya and avocado salad
directions: Combine papaya, mandarins and avocados in bowl.
Beat together remaining ingredients until well blended, pour over mixture. Cover and refrigerate several hours, turning mixture 2 or 3 times. Serve on bed of bok choy or lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: harvest pound cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add baby food.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Put both mixtures together and mix well. Add pecans and bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: herb rau's world's greatest brunswick stew
directions: In heavy pot, saute onions in a little oil until onions are transparent.
Then add everything, except the corn.
Stir well. Simmer about 2 hours or until stew is thick.
Then add the corn and simmer another 30 minutes.
If stew is too thin, add potato flakes to thicken.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: gram's green beans
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until heated through.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: In a nonstick skillet, bring carrot and water to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Add the broccoli, onion and zucchini; return to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 minutes. Add salad dressing and oregano. Cook and stir over medium heat for 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender and liquid is reduced.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit in bowl.
Mix dry ingredients.
Pour melted margarine over fruit; then add dry ingredients.
Mix all together. Pour into a large, greased glass baking dish.

title: giant blowing bubbles
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use plastic pop can holder or a wire twisted into a circle.
Have fun.

title: striped chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of the peanut butter and butter until smooth. Stir in cracker crumbs; cool.
Press mixture onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.
In a 1-quart saucepan, combine vanilla pudding and 1 1/2 cups of the milk.
Cook and stir to a full boil.
Stir in remaining peanut butter.
Spoon into crust. Chill.
Combine chocolate pudding and remaining milk; cook and stir to a full boil.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon over peanut butter layer.
Chill.
To serve, spread dessert topping over pie; sprinkle with chopped nuts and chocolate curls, if desired.

title: hillbilly steaks
directions: Combine all of the above in a bowl.
Use your fingers, it's easier than a spoon.
Make into patties and fry in a skillet until well done.
Remove from skillet and put patties in a bowl.
Leave drippings in the skillet and add 3 beef boullion cubes with 2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil after cubes dissolve.
Thicken with corn starch & water.
When gravy is done, pour over steaks and serve with mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 patties.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Add Cool Whip last.
Chill and serve!

title: spinach salad
directions: Blend vinegar, oil, sugar, catsup and Worcestershire and add to salad just before serving.

title: ham and cheese appetizers(makes 36)
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: holiday punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix together pineapple juice, champagne, wine and grenadine.
Add ice cubes.
Float lemon and orange slices on top.
Add mint for garnish.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: heavenly vegetable casserole
directions: Mix soups, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: good punch
directions: Mix together ingredients and just before serving, add 7-Up. You can make this punch 2 days ahead of time.
Reminder that the 7-Up needs to be COLD.

title: christmas morning breakfast
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place bread in dish, lining the bottom.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread layer.
Spoon sausage over egg layer. Top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stir-fry chicken and vegetables
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
In large frying pan, place oil and heat to medium-high temperature.
Add chicken and garlic and stir-fry about 3 minutes or until chicken loses its pink color.
Add carrots, broccoli, celery and onion; continue cooking about 5 minutes, stirring constantly through entire process. Sprinkle with pepper and soy sauce.
Pour chicken broth over contents in frying pan.
When liquid begins to boil, add bean sprouts and mushrooms.
Heat about 2 minutes.
Vegetables should remain crisp.
Do not overcook.
Serve over rice.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix until dissolved.
Roll thinner than regular biscuits.
Dip biscuits in melted margarine.
Stack 2 high; let stand 15 minutes. Bake at 450°.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve between buns or over rice or noodles.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound steak between wax paper to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut into 6 pieces. Coat steak with flour/salt/pepper mixture. Heat oil in large skillet. Brown steak well on both sides. Move to one side of skillet and saute onion until tender. Add tomatoes and broth. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add carrots; cover and simmer for 1/2 hour or until tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and mix.
Do not beat. Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 18 medium muffins.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large Mason jar.
Shake well. Two tablespoons in a cup with hot water.

title: golden egg bread
directions: In bread machine pan, place all ingredients in order suggested. Select basic bread setting. Bake according to bread machine directions.

title: pumpkin crunch cake
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle one box yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture. Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Thinly slice margarine over nuts. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add pumpkin, sugars and oil.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Spoon into paper-lined muffin pans filled 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot soup
directions: Heat oil or butter in a pan and cook onion until soft (5 minutes).
Add water, potatoes and carrots.
Cover.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Blend in a blender.
Return ingredients to pot and add milk.
Warm over low heat and add pepper and dill.

title: monkey cake
directions: Combine 3/4 c. brown sugar & cinnamon in bag. Shake a few quarters of biscuits at a time in the bag. Put in a well greased angel food or bundt pan. Bring remaining 1 c. brown sugar and 1 1/2 sticks margarine to a boil and pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from pan immediately; serve warm (invert on plate with sides).
Raisins or nuts may also be added.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: cream of squash and carrot soup
directions: Dice onion.
Cook over medium heat in one tablespoon salad oil until tender about 15 minutes.
Remove onion to plate.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse and drain.
Add drained tuna, thawed peas and pickles.
Mix and add Miracle Whip to desired taste.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and put in a large microwave dish.
Mix all other ingredients together, except almonds.
Put mixed ingredients into microwave dish.
Add almonds on top.
Cook on High for 20 minutes.

title: brown sugar date cookies
directions: Filling:
Combine dates, 1/2 cup white sugar and water.
Boil until thick and cool.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add all other ingredients, mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind vegetables together; add salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain in the morning.
Boil vinegar, sugar and spice bag.
Pour over pepper mixture; bring to a boil.
Boil 15 minutes.
Jar and seal (1/2 peck equals 1 quart).

title: sausage braid
directions: Cook sausage, onions, green pepper and garlic until sausage is no longer pink.
Drain well. Add cream cheese until melted. Set aside.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks in the top of a double boiler.
Add sugar and cook until thickened.
Add the salt to the egg whites, whip until stiff.
Pour the hot custard over them.
Return the custard to the double boiler.
Beat and cook until it is thickened and stands up well.
Fold in strawberries.
Fill pie shell.
Brown the pie in a hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned osgood pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter, vinegar, egg yolks, cloves, cinnamon, pecans and dates.
Add 4 slightly beaten (5 seconds or so) egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until set.
Makes one large deep dish pie.
If egg whites are beaten too long, the top crust of the pie will crack and break.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Have flour mixed with the sugar before adding to mixture.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Next, add milk to which enough water has been added to make a total of 3 1/2 cups of liquid.
Next, add desired amount of chocolate syrup.
Cook over low heat until it boils and is thick.
Pour into crusts that have already been baked.
Makes 2 good 9-inch pies.
(Instead of chocolate, coconut may be added.)

title: potato surprise
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, soups, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crush cereal and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Combine buttermilk, salt and pepper; stir well. Skin chicken, if desired. Place chicken in a shallow container and pour mixture over top. Cover and let stand 20 minutes, turning once. Remove chicken.

title: raisin nut bars
directions: Combine raisins and water.
Stir in salad oil or margarine. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and beat into raisin mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until done at 375°.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
When blended, stir in sour cream.
Mix together in separate bowl the brown and white sugar, nuts and cinnamon.

title: chicken broccoli delight
directions: Simmer chicken in water until tender.
Drain, bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain off liquid.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks of the margarine. Add soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Melt remaining margarine; mix with bread crumbs.
Place alternate layers of chicken, broccoli, stuffing mix and soup mixture in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or large casserole, ending with soup mixture. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Cook in a glass pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: maraschino cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and whip with cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and blend well.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows and cherries.

title: salmon puff
directions: Bake until set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Double recipe, 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco Butter good- Beat one egg at a time alternating flour and sour cream.
Beat well each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a well greased floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 300 degrees for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: crab soup
directions: Place all ingredients except crabmeat in a large pan and simmer uncovered until vegetables are done.
Gently mix in crabmeat and simmer until heated through.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: tupperware pie crust
directions: Shake for 45 seconds in covered bowl (like Tupperware), then add 1/4 cup water plus little bit and shake 30 seconds.
Comes out perfect every time.
Make 2 crusts.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and add ice cubes until mixture reaches one quart level.
Blend to desired consistency.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mix all together.
Best if left overnight.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: asparagus lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Trim asparagus.
Cut stalks into 1-inch pieces.
Remove 1-1/2 cups of the asparagus tips.
Set aside.
In a large pot of boiling water, cook the remaining asparagus for 3 minutes.
Drain and refresh under cold water. Drain again.

title: pineapple casserole(like a bread pudding)
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine and add other ingredients.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use as a side dish or serve with whipped cream as a dessert.
Delicious hot with ham.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions and let cool.

In the meantime, line Pyrex dish (9 x 13-inch) with graham crackers (if necessary, it's okay to break crackers in half to fit Pyrex). Spread cooled chocolate pudding over crackers, then put another row of crackers on top of chocolate pudding.
Spread cooled vanilla pudding on top of crackers and add crackers on top of vanilla pudding and refrigerate.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Chill mixture for 2 hours or until firm. Drain cherries;
dry
on
paper
towels.
Place bowl of sugar mixture in
a
bowl
of ice to keep mixture chilled.
Shape a small amount
of
sugar mixture around each cherry.
Place on waxed paper
lined cookie sheet; chill about 2 hours or until firm. Melt
chocolate and shortening in top of double boiler. Dip
each cherry
by
stem
into chocolate.
Place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet; chill until firm.
Store cherries in a cool place. Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: crab mousse
directions: Make this appetizer using any 4-cup mold or two (2 cup) molds. Coat the molds with cooking spray and set aside.

title: pink lady
directions: Whip all ingredients except celery together in blender 2 minutes, then serve.
Garnish with celery for a dieter's lunch. Serves 6.

title: choco-nut delites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour and salt on waxed paper. Beat together margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla in large bowl until well mixed.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Shape dough on lightly floured surface into logs (2 x 1/2-inch).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Dip ends of cookies into Chocolate Coating; roll ends in chopped nuts.
Place on waxed paper until set.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Slice meat across grain in thin strips.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over meat.
Soak for 24 hours in refrigerator or 8 hours at room temperature.
Turn halfway through soak.
Cook over grill.

title: orange cake
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and butter together.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with orange juice to the cream mixture.
Add egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Fold in egg whites.
Can also make coconut cake.
(Instead of orange juice, use coconut milk.)

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix all but cornflakes and 1/4 cup oleo.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cornflakes and melted oleo.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: old-fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour all into pie shell and bake at 300° for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pat chicken dry and season with salt and pepper to taste.
In large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, melt 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine.
Add chicken; cook 1 1/2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Stir in broth and Marsala; reduce heat to medium-low and simmer about 2 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: garlic-cheese bread
directions: Cut bread lengthwise in half.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes until lightly browned.
Mix other ingredients and spread on bread. Resume broiling 2 minutes until desired brown.
Cut crosswise and serve.

title: heath bar ice cream dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and stick of butter.
Press on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften ice cream.
Mix with Heath bars, crushed. Spread over crust and freeze.
Heat chocolate topping and pour over each serving.
Top with Cool Whip.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: meat balls
directions: In small skillet over medium heat, saute pepper and onion in butter or margarine 3 minutes.
Set aside.
In bowl, mix together ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper until wet.
Combine onion and peppers.
Form into 6 small oval shaped loaves, about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Place in ungreased baking pan, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Serve with mashed potatoes and gravy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine eggs, soup, mayonnaise, onion and 3/4 cup cheese.
Pour over cooked broccoli and stir until blended.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
During the last 10 minutes of baking, top with cracker crumbs and remaining cheese.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar, cover and shake well. Keep refrigerated up to one month. Shake before serving.

title: marinated oysters
directions: Place oysters in a large container.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight, stirring at least twice.
Serve with crackers.
This makes an easy and delicious "party starter".

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed.
Then add carrots and celery.
Put in refrigerator.

title: blueberry cake muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
With paper liners, line 8 muffin pan cups or grease them well.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat butter with granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture (in fourths), alternately with milk (in thirds), beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat until just smooth.
Gently fold in blueberries. Make sure to grease the top of the muffin pan as well as muffin cups.
Fill each muffin cup 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove muffins to wire rack; let cool slightly.
Serve warm or cold, sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Makes 8 large muffins.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: mexican baked beans
directions: Combine all the ingredients together, except the bacon strips. Stir well until blended.
Use 1 1/2-quart casserole dish or a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish.
Put all ingredients into the casserole and place bacon strips across the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly or until desired consistency.
Hot sauce depends on your own taste.

title: baked coffee custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, instant coffee and vanilla.
Add milk gradually, stirring vigorously.
Pour into custard cups. Place in pan of hot water and bake in 375° oven for about 20 minutes.
Chill thoroughly.
Unmold on serving dishes, if desired. Also good with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Mix into hot, drained broccoli, the American cheese (in pieces), 1/2 stick butter and minced onion.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Fry ground beef.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix.
In small mixing bowl, combine beans and taco sauce.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press rolls on
a large cookie sheet.
Do not separate rolls. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread over completely cooled rolls.
Sprinkle veggies and yellow cheese over the cream cheese mixture.
Cut into 2 to 3-inch squares when ready to serve.

title: bacon and tomato cup
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 2 mini-muffin tins. Combine all ingredients, except biscuits, in medium bowl. Separate each biscuit into 2 biscuits.
Flatten and place in muffin tin.
Fill each with bacon mixture.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices. Wash and chop raisins, dust with small amount of flour mixture. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add flour mixture alternately with soup and stir until smooth.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until done.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine olive oil and garlic and let sit 1/2 hour.
Add lemon juice from lemons, egg, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir well.
Tear 2 heads of romaine lettuce and arrange in bowl.
Strain dressing into lettuce and toss.
Top with Romano cheese and croutons and serve.

title: eloise's chili dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in 8 or 9 inch pan.
Add chopped onion and green pepper, followed by chili sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Roll graham crackers into crumbs.
Combine margarine, crumbs and 1/4 cup sugar and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and remaining sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over graham cracker mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool.
Spread on pie filling. Mix Dream Whip according to directions and spread on top.
Chill 4 to 5 hours and serve.

title: shanghai
directions: Brown beef and onion in pan.
Cook rice, then combine all ingredients and mix.
Put in oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in cup of boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries. Chill until set. Melt marshmallows in milk, using low heat. Cool.
Whip the Dream Whip as directed and add to cool marshmallows.
Work graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar and margarine together.
Line bottom of a 9-inch square pan with the crumbs (save 1/3 cup for topping).
Put Jell-O mixture on top of crumbs, then marshmallow mixture and sprinkle with the crumbs.

title: hamburg stew
directions: Soften bread in hot milk.
Break up with fork; add 1 beaten egg and mix into hamburg.
Form into four cakes.
Dust with flour and brown on both sides.
Add tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer a few minutes.
Add diced potatoes, carrots and small whole onions.
Season and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Combine crackers and oleo.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture. Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl until blended; beat 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients except carrots and nuts; beat 1 minute.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: crescent pinwheels
directions: Press crescent roll dough into 4 rectangles.
Mix cream cheese, cut up meat and other ingredients into bowl.
Spread cream cheese mixture on crescent roll rectangles.
Roll into 4 logs. Refrigerate about 1 hour, then slice into little pinwheel shapes. Put on cookie sheet and bake in 375° preheated oven for 20 minutes until slightly brown.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Dust cranberries and nuts with flour.
Place juice and rind of orange into measuring cup and add boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Blend butter and sugar until creamy.
Add slightly beaten egg, then orange juice mixture. Blend this with nuts and cranberries into dry ingredients.
Place in a greased small loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: turkey and rice quiche(makes 8 servings; 16 triangles)
directions: Combine rice, turkey, tomato, onions, green pepper, basil, salt, ground red pepper, milk and eggs in 13 x 9-inch pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. To serve, cut quiche into 8 squares; cut each square diagonally into 2 triangles.
Garnish as desired.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch together in a saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until glaze boils and thickens.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello, stir until dissolved.
Pour over fresh fruit in baked 9-inch pie shell. Refrigerate; top with whipped topping after pie is cool if desired.

title: rocky road
directions: Put chocolate in a medium nonmetal bowl.
Cook in microwave on High for 2 minutes, stirring once or until chocolate is melted. Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: calas
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by small teaspoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll in powdered sugar or cinnamon and sugar.
Excellent warm with coffee or milk.
Eaten with fingers.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Combine graham crackers, butter and sugar.
Mixture should be moist, but not wet.
Press into bottom and up sides of spring-form pan. Set aside.
Combine whipped topping, pudding and sour cream in bowl with whisk.
Pour half of filling over the crust.
Layer bananas on top.
Pour remaining filling over bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts. Sets immediately but can be refrigerated to chill.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix in large bowl all ingredients.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Cut grapes in half; remove seeds.
Add grapes, marshmallows, nuts and whipped cream to cranberries.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown together and drain the ground beef and onions.
Simmer together tomatoes and liquid, tomato paste, water, garlic, salt, basil leaves, rosemary and sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make alternate layers of noodles, cheeses and meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dave's bread
directions: Spread slices of bread on cookie sheet.
Spread with butter. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Top with tomatoes.
Broil until brown.

title: christmas quickies
directions: Mix all ingredients well; roll into 1-inch balls and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Make a thin icing with powdered sugar, a few drops of vanilla and milk; add a few drops of green food coloring.
Spread on cookies.

title: pancake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in gallon jars.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons of mix.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg yolks, salt and vanilla. Stir, then add flour last.
Spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Immediately place chocolate bars on top; allow them to melt and spread chocolate.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut while hot.

title: baby pink salad
directions: In large bowl, soften gelatin in strawberry juice.
Drain pineapple, placing the juice in a small saucepan.
Heat pineapple juice to a boil, then remove from heat.
Add to the softened gelatin.
Stir to dissolve.
Stir in lemon juice and salt.
Put in refrigerator.
When mixture starts to thicken, fold in pineapple, strawberries, marshmallows and firmly whipped cream.
Turn into a jello mold and chill.
Serve when firm.
Serves 12.

title: easy chicken fajitas
directions: Mix together and let stand for 5 minutes.
Warm fajita shells. Fill and roll up.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pack into a greased small loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Serve with tartar sauce, if desired.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add to eggs.
Scald 1/2 gallon of milk and pour over egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Put into top of double boiler and cook over hot water (not boiling) for 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture coats the spoon. Strain hot mixture in a cheesecloth.
Cool and add the half and half cream and flavor.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and slice pickles; put in gallon glass jar.
Boil remaining ingredients.
Pour over pickles; let cool.
Put in refrigerator and stir the first four days.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan (glass pan works best).
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Mix the sugar, 4 tablespoons flour and baking powder together; add to the beaten eggs, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Mix well; spread over cooked crust.
Bake again for 25 minutes at 350°. Makes 96 desserts.

title: microwave fudge sauce
directions: In 3-quart casserole, stir together sugar, salt and milk until blended. Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes until boiling hard. Stir into boiling mixture the chocolate until completely melted. Stir in butter and vanilla. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Mix and
bake
in
(9-inch)
round pans for 25 to 30 minutes at
(Also,
can use 2 round pans, but better to use round pans than oblong ones.) Cool cake before frosting.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish; then mix all ingredients in dish.
Sprinkle
top with cinnamon and/or nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for
approximately
to
minutes by checking with toothpick.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° until done.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown beef and refried beans with bacon grease.
Place mixture and all other ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or on low up to 6 hours.

title: sour milk pancakes(a family favorite!)
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender.
Cover and process at mix until well blended.
Bake on a lightly greased griddle until nicely browned.
Turn only once.

title: peanut or pecan brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 4 minutes.
Add nuts and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Microwave on Medium 2 to 3 minutes more.
Remove and quickly stir in baking soda.
Spread brittle evenly on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Allow brittle to cool and harden for 1 hour.
Break brittle into pieces.
Store in refrigerator to keep fresh.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat egg slightly; add salt and flour, enough to make stiff dough.
Roll our paper thin and cut; let stand 20 minutes.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Cover with cold water; let stand 2 hours.
Drain well and rinse.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup vinegar; mix well.
Do not heat.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: cracked wheat bread
directions: If you choose, you can use 1 cup whole-wheat flour, 4 1/2 cups unbleached flour and 2 tablespoons wheat germ.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, peanuts and salt in iron skillet until it changes color to light brown, stirring constantly.
Take from heat and add vinegar and baking soda.
Pour on Pam-sprayed cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break in pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Put all ingredients in large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. (May need to add enough water to cover ingredients.) Cover. Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.

title: molasses snaps
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add potatoes and continue creaming.
Mix in molasses.
Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Stir into first mixture.
Drop the batter by tablespoon on greased baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass to 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until cookies are brown.

title: popover
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pizza sauce over top.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sauce.

title: fudge
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar.
Add salt and milk.
boil until forms soft round ball in water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Beat until creamy; can put pan in cold water to help cool down but beat constantly.
Pour on buttered platter.

title: honey peanut shake
directions: Combine all ingredients into an electric blender.
Cover and blend until foamy.
Pour into a tall, chilled glass.
Serve.

title: cole slaw
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients as listed in airtight bowl.
Combine last 3 ingredients; boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over slaw and do not stir.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix dry mustard with vinegar.
Combine with all ingredients. Pour into baking dish.
Place onion in center.
Put bacon on top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook onion in water in skillet until transparent, set aside. Microwave broccoli following package directions for 6 minutes; drain. Prepare rice following package directions omitting 2 teaspoons margarine. Melt margarine in a large saucepan; remove from heat. Add salt and flour, stirring until smooth. Add milk gradually, stirring until well blended. Return to heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in cheese and cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Add onions, broccoli and rice; mix well. Spray a
1 1/2 qt. baking dish with non-stick cooking spray. Pour broccoli mixture into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix together; make balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: pineapple-lime cooler
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Serve over ice or float pineapple ice ring.
Serves 10.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, oil, sugars and eggs. Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix into creamed mixture thoroughly. Chill dough at least 1 hour until ready to bake.

title: wonton soup
directions: In medium pan, bring chicken broth, soy sauce (salt) and 2 cups water to boil.
If 4 cups of broth, omit water.
Cook wontons and place in bowl.
Pour broth over wontons and garnish with pieces of scallions.

title: baked mandarins
directions: Soak mandarins in cold water for 2 hours.
Neatly, cut off top about 1/4 down.
Loosen peel and fruit, fill all spaces with sugar, top with 1/8 teaspoon butter.
Place mandarins in baking dish filled with water to approximately 1/4-inch up side of the mandarin.

Cover with aluminum foil, bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Be sure to keep the bottom of the baking dish covered with water. Remove mandarins from pan, thicken pan juices with arrowroot, flavor with juice or sherry.
Put mandarins under broiler to brown top slightly.
Serve with hot syrup.
Serves 8.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Place sweetened milk into bowl.
Roll bread strips in milk. Roll into coconut.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Make sure cookie sheet is greased.

title: cracker crisp salmon salad
directions: Wash and drain greens early in day and chill in a crisper. Mash garlic and salt together until garlic disintegrates.
Add salt mix to mayonnaise, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce. Chill. Mix all and add dressing and crackers when ready to serve.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Mix other ingredients.
Make into small balls on cookie sheet.
Put into refrigerator to cool.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Whip eggs with a fork lightly.
Add milk, salt and flour (a little at a time).
Stir with a fork.
Add and stir until a soft ball is formed.
It may be kneaded on a board for a few minutes. Cut in 2 parts and roll up on floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in squares and drop in boiling broth.
Simmer 45 minutes or until tender.

title: fresh strawberry dessert
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Fold pineapple and Cool Whip together.
Break cake up into small pieces.
Mix cake, cheese mixture and pineapple mixture together.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut strawberries up (not too small).
Mix with glaze and put on top of mixture in pan.
Chill.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth and thick. Use in place of Eagle Brand milk.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sand pie
directions: Mix together butter, flour and pecans.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 cups Cool Whip.
Put in cooled crust.
Prepare pudding and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top pie with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix together; fill ungreased muffin tins 2/3 full (or use cupcake wrappers).
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable and black bean burritos
directions: Saut all ingredients, kind of stir-fry style.
Fill steamed flour tortillas. Top with sour cream and salsa.

title: 1015 onion casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Spray nonstick vegetable spray on a large shallow casserole dish (2-quart). Layer crackers, sausage and onions. Mix soup with milk and pour over layers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: ham, chicken or tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together, except potato chips.
Put into 3 cup casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, on Medium for 14 to 16 1/2 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Stir once or twice.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish and cover with soup and mushrooms.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove drippings and add 1 cup sour cream.
Heat on low on top of the stove.
Serve chicken with sour cream mixture and wild rice.

title: annie wynn's pickles
directions: Drain, rinse and slice pickles into 1/4-inch slices.
Put back in jar; add all other ingredients.
Refrigerate; keep shaking and turning to melt sugar.

title: chicken gizzard curry
directions: Place oil in skillet.
Add sliced onion and saute.
Add curry and quartered gizzards.
Cook until onion is done.
Add both tomato sauce and tomato paste and 1 large can of water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Add water, if needed.
Add more curry to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: chunky apple cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar; mix well.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, vanilla and apples.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in single layer in buttered pan.
Top with onion slices.
Mix remaining ingredients in small saucepan; heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken skin side up.
Baste with sauce in pan; continue baking, basting once or twice, for 30 minutes longer, until tender and richly glazed.
(I remove skin before cooking.)

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles with elongated points toward center of a greased 12-inch pizza pan or pie dish.
Press bottom and sides to form crust; seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on lower oven rack.
Crust will be puffy when removed from oven.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs with next 3 ingredients; pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° on lower rack for 30 to 35 minutes.
Garnish with pepper slices, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: coney island barbecue
directions: Brown meat in a small amount of oil.
Remove from pan, then add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook until tender, then stir in meat.
Add tomato soup, salt and pepper to taste, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and chili powder.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over buns, rice or beans.
I usually use rice.

title: frosted banana bars
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: good lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package; drain. Combine oregano with spaghetti sauce.
In greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch pan, alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and sauce.
Have sauce on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Then add pie filling and nuts instead of cold water.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: coppa tuna salad
directions: Pour olive oil in mixing bowl.
Mash drained tuna in oil.
Add garlic salt, parsley flakes, onion, celery, eggs, salt and pepper. Mix lightly.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse, then add to olive oil mixture.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten (additional salt and pepper may be needed).
Refrigerate overnight for best taste. Serve with crackers.

title: punch
directions: Mix well the acid, sugar and boiling water.
Add the cold water and juices.
This makes 4 1/2 gallons undiluted.
Use 1 bottle ginger ale to 1 gallon punch.
Put in freezer and let freeze, thawing partially just before serving.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Place apples in buttered 8 x 8 in. pan.
Remove crust from bread and cut into 5 finger wedges.
Place bread over apples.
Mix sugar, flour, egg and butter.
Pour over bread.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Any other fruit may be used as well.

title: tommie lynn's ice cream
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Fill with regular milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: caramel nut brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler over barely simmering water.
Stir frequently.
Combine cake mix with melted butter and remaining 1/3 cup milk.
Spread half of this mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: humpty-dumpty egg breakfast
directions: Soft-boil eggs; make sure the yolk is fluid.
Make toast and smear with butter; cut into 1-inch wide longitudinal strips.
When eggs are soft-boiled, place them into the Humpty-Dumpty egg holders.
Crack open and peel off top 1/4 of egg shell to expose delicious liquid yolk.
Add salt and pepper to taste to egg yolk.

title: orange balls("no bake")
directions: Roll wafers fine.
Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in water and mayonnaise. Mix well.
Grease and flour 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until done, 30 or more minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place pie filling in middle of tortillas.
In a saucepan, cook (or heat until sugar melts) the sugar, water, oleo and vanilla. Roll tortillas with fruit and place, side by side, in casserole. Pour mixture over rolled tortillas.
Cook, covered, at 350°, then uncovered for 30 minutes.
(Total cooking time:
1 hour.)

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt until well blended.
Chill approximately 1 hour and serve with favorite fruits.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thickened. Set in pan of ice water to cool. Wash strawberries and slice; place slices in the 2 baked pie crusts. When jello mixture is cool, pour over strawberries. Chill overnight and serve with Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter flavored Crisco, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in a large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Scrape sides of bowl frequently.
Add egg and milk; beat until well blended. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls of dough on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: power-packed peanut bars
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan and set aside. In large bowl, mix together rice cereal, oats and peanuts. Place peanut butter, brown sugar and corn syrup in small saucepan over low heat. Stir constantly until smooth and just starts to boil. Stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal mixture. Gently toss to mix well. Pour into prepared pan and press level. Cool completely. Cut into 12 bars.

title: health salad
directions: Slice the shredded cabbage, carrots, onion, cucumbers and pepper thin.
Salt to taste.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Combine baking powder, salt, soda and flour.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, sugar and yeast mixture.
Knead dough slightly.
Put in covered bowl in refrigerator.
When chilled, roll out and cut.
Bake very slowly about 200° until done.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator several days.

title: 4-hour dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 tablespoons sugar in 1/4 cup warm water. Add yeast mixture to remaining ingredients.
Let rise 2 hours in warm place.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: cocoa sherbet
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme and cocoa in top of double boiler until Creme is melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; add milk and stir until well blended.
Pour into container of ice cream machine and freeze.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread half in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except spinach) in bowl.
Add spinach. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Cut up choice of raw fruit; dip and eat.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups water and raisins in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil until water evaporates.
Remove from heat. Add applesauce, eggs, Sweet 'N Low, oil and remaining 1/2 cup water.
Stir until well combined.
Sift flour, cinnamon and soda. Gradually add to applesauce with vanilla, stirring after each addition.
Spoon into a 10-inch Bundt pan coated with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on a wire rack.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan melt margarine; saute onion and garlic.
Stir in 1/4 cup olives, chilies, sour cream and soup.
Mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup sauce.
Fold in chicken and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Warm tortillas.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Place seam side down in ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In small bowl combine reserved sauce and milk.
Spoon over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with remaining cheese and olives.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Crush cornflakes and pour margarine over it.
Steam cabbage just enough to wilt. Drain.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over cabbage. Spread cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
