title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple and combine juice of pineapple with marshmallows and jello; stir over low heat until all are dissolved. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add cottage cheese, drained pineapple and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in pan, chill until firm, cut in 2-inch squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; mash.
Add milk and whip.
Add butter, eggs, seasonings, onions and 1 cup cheese; mix well.

title: fudge icing
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
(Boil cannot be stirred down.)
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat and beat until mixture starts to thicken and cool.
Spread on cake.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Chop beef and onion in blender.
Mix cream cheese, onion, Accent and Worcestershire sauce and some of chipped beef.
Save some to roll cheese ball in.

title: nut rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, water, salt and sugar in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until scalded.
Stir in remaining ingredients; remove from heat.
Cover.
Let stand at least 20 minutes.
Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: red bean pie
directions: Mix sugar and egg yolks until creamy.
Add the red beans, stir well.
Add flour and salt.
Add 1/2 cup milk slowly and vanilla. Cook until it thickens.
Pour into baked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar to whites, dash of salt and vanilla.
Cover pie.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: magic squares
directions: Combine melted butter, graham crumbs and coconut.
Press lightly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with layer of chocolate bits and sprinkle with nuts.
Drizzle condensed milk evenly over surface.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or lightly browned at edges.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Cook shoulder in a slow cooker, in water, overnight; cool. Discard all fat, skin, bones and gristle.
Leave liquid in fridge overnight; discard fat.
(Can be thickened for gravy and seasoning for pork chops.)
Shred meat or cut across grain.
Add salsa and vinegar to taste.
Package and freeze.
Thaw, reheat and serve on hamburger buns.
Sprinkle with Texas Pete hot sauce.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: summer squash bread
directions: Cut squash into chunks and cook until tender in lightly salted water.
Drain well and mince.
Place squash in mixing bowl and add eggs, milk, salt and cottage cheese.
Stir in corn bread mix and spoon mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart shallow glass baking dish.
Pour margarine over top and bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Rub in butter.
Knead to form a smooth paste (use your hands).
Flatten onto a cookie sheet (11 x 16-inch).
Prick all over with a fork.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes, until pale golden color.
Remove from oven; cut into fingers while still in pan.
Cool.
Will make up to 72.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until half done.
Peel and dice into large cubes.
Place in casserole.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, chop onion, bell pepper and tomatoes. Combine oil and vinegar.
Add garlic powder and oregano to taste.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix well and pour over potatoes.
Cover.
Bake until potatoes are done, about 1 hour.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cheese, cream, salt, vanilla, sugar and egg yolks.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff.
Fold cream mixture into egg whites.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Cool in oven 1 hour.
Top with cherry pie filling. Serve with whipped cream.

title: new york cream cheesecake
directions: Combine in a mixing bowl, Cream Cheese, Eggs, 1 tsp.
Vanilla and 2/3 c. Sugar.
Beat well about 5 minutes.
Place in Pie Crust and bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Iincrease oven temperature to 400 degrees.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Combine in a mixing bowl, Sour Cream, 1/3 c. Sugar, and 1 tsp.
Vanilla, mix well. Pour mixture over cooled Pie, then place in 400 degree oven for 10 minutes.
Remove Pie and chill.

title: mannie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat shortening and butter for 30 seconds; add egg, milk and vanilla. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture.
Beat until well combined.
Stir in oats and walnuts.
Chill dough for two hours.
Form 1-inch balls.
Dip top of ball in additional granulated sugar (optional).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: party scrabble mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a large brown paper grocery sack. Shake well. Mix remaining ingredients together in a saucepan and heat to melt margarine.

title: fudge(makes 5 pounds)
directions: Stir until dissolved and pour into greased pans.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: banana drink
directions: Combine yogurt, banana, milk and orange juice concentrate in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: First Day:
Slice cucumbers and soak in lime water for 24 hours in 1 gallon of water to 1 cup lime.

title: ding-dong cake
directions: Cut Ding-Dongs in half.
Place, creamy side down, in a rectangular pan.
Make chocolate pudding according to directions on box.
Pour pudding over Ding-Dongs.
Spread whipped cream over pudding.
Let chill.
Serve.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all together. To make an ice mold, use 2 to 3 cups of mixture, place in ring shaped mold with fruit and freeze the night before. Place the ring in punch bowl and pour mixture over it.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Bring milk and butter to boil; remove from stove to cool. Beat 4 eggs, gradually adding sugar and salt.
Add flavorings, beating well.
Stir in flour, then add warm milk and butter.
Do not have it hot.
Add the baking powder last, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake in 350° oven from 40 minutes to an hour.
(Depends on your oven.)

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix corn bread ingredients together and set aside.
Brown meat and onion.
Then add other ingredients.
Cook until all liquid is gone.
Prepare pan.
Grease pan.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of corn meal.
Pour half corn meal mixture in pan.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle 1 (8 ounce) package of Cheddar cheese on top of meat.
Then pour rest of corn meal mixture on top.
Cook 45 minutes at 375°.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In separate bowl, mix the pudding and milk together until thick.
Combine cream cheese mixture, pudding mixture and other ingredients.
With blender, blend cookies until they resemble "dirt," using the inside of cookies also.
Put aluminum foil on a plastic flowerpot, lining entire inside.
Put a layer of cookies in bottom, then other mixture, alternating each layer, ending with cookies on top.
You can put aluminum foil around the stems of silk flowers and put them into the "dirt."

title: baked squash
directions: Drain and mash squash; add oleo.
Combine flour, eggs, milk, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add to squash and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Put tomatoes through food chopper.
Add salt and mix.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, drain off juice.
Put onions and peppers through food chopper.
Add to tomatoes with sugar, vinegar and spice (tied in a bag).
Cook to boiling point; reduce heat and simmer 3 hours.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: sugar & spice pecans
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well with spoon.
Add pecans; stir until evenly coated.
Spread in a greased 15x10x1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 275° for 50-55 minutes. Remove to waxed paper and break apart while still warm; cool. Store in an airtight container.
Yield 9-10 cups.

title: walnut butter cookies
directions: Cut together as for a pie crust the flour, sugar, salt and butter.
Add liquid coffee and mix.
Shape into walnut-size balls. Roll in chopped walnuts.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
A nice holiday cookie.

title: beef hash
directions: Put beef roast and onion in pot and cover with water.
Cook until onion is done.
Add sage, salt and black pepper.
In a pint jar, mix flour and water.
Shake to mix good so you won't have lumps, in thickening.
While water in beef is slowly boiling, pour in flour mixture until it starts to thicken.
Take off heat.

title: tonya marcum's pizza snack
directions: Fry sausage and drain grease well.
Add cheese, ketchup, oregano and garlic. Simmer until cheese melts.
Spread on party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: trifle
directions: Make puddings according to directions on package; use slightly less milk.
Crush Oreo cookies and layer in the bottom of a bowl, then add instant chocolate pudding.
Next, add Cool Whip.
Crush vanilla wafers and layer over Cool Whip, then add instant vanilla pudding.
Add more Cool Whip and top with three Oreo cookies.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Put in butter and sugar, then add oil.
Then beat in eggs, one at a time, then add in almond and lemon flavorings.
Pour into mixture along with the 7-Up.
Mix well; put into Bundt cake pan at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: hearty soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large sauce pan, brown beef, then drain. Add the remaining ingredients except green beans.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Bring back to a boil and cook about 15 more minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yield:
about 2 quarts.

title: peanut butter butterscotch cookies(no baking needed)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the peanut butter and the butterscotch pieces.
Put the saucepan on the stove over medium heat.
Stir the mixture until it is completely melted and mixed. Remove the saucepan from the heat and stir in the cornflakes. Stir well.
Put waxed paper onto cookie sheets. Drop the batter from a teaspoon onto the waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour for the cookies to harden. Serve.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix beans with 1 to 2 tablespoons salsa until creamy.
Spread on bottom of container (quiche dish works perfectly).
Cover bean with layer of salsa.
Next, layer green onions.
Spread sour cream over onion layer.
Cover entire top with cheese.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving to let flavors set.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Layer cukes, onions, peppers and salt in pan or crock-pot.
Not aluminum!
Place a layer of ice in between each layer (approximately 4 layers).
Chill for 3 hours or refrigerate overnight.
Drain.
Prepare syrup mixture of remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat to boiling. Cook 3 minutes until heated through.
Seal in sterilized jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: tofu pumpkin pie
directions: The kids won't even know they're eating healthy.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Put water, beef and barley in a large pot.
Stir to break up meat. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 50 to 60 minutes or until barley is tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: herb or spice jelly
directions: In a small saucepan over high heat, bring 1 cup fruit juice to a boil.
Pour over herbs or spice and let stand for 20 minutes; strain into large saucepan.
Add vinegar, the last 2 cups of fruit juice and coloring (if desired).
Mix in sugar.
Bring to a boil. Stir in pectin and boil 1 minute more.
Remove from heat; skim off foam.
Pour into hot jars.
Add sprig or few leaves of herbs.
Seal jars.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Cover bottom of pan with coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix according to box directions. Pour over coconut and pecans.
In large bowl, cream together cream cheese and butter.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Spoon over cake batter.
Do not stir.
Cook in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: rye bread pizza
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger; drain off grease.
Add cheese, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and oregano.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press crumbs with 1 stick of melted margarine into oblong dish.

title: diabetes crock-pot apple butter
directions: Heap crock-pot with the chopped apples (lid may not fit at the start).
Drizzle the sweetener, cinnamon and salt over the apples. Cook on high all day until apples are dark and thick.
Stir occasionally.
Place in small jars and seal.
Process at 5 pound pressure in pressure cooker about 10 minutes.
Yields 32 (2 tablespoon) servings.

title: ham-olive roll-ups
directions: Spread a generous amount
of cream cheese on each piece of ham.
Cut each slice into
6 strips.
Place an olive at the end of each strip and roll
like
a
jelly
roll.
Secure with cocktail picks.

title: rare beef tenderloin
directions: Take beef tenderloin from wrapper (still cool).
Salt and pepper tenderloin.
Then cover entire tenderloin with Kitchen Bouquet (rub it in with your hand well).
Tuck tip of tenderloin under and place whole tenderloin on a wire rack in baking pan. Let cool to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Place tenderloin in oven and immediately reduce temperature to 450°. Cook for 30 minutes only, then remove from oven and cover with foil.
Let sit 20 to 30 minutes and then slice thinly.
Beef will be rare and melt in your mouth.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Combine together and put into a greased pound cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: hazelnut torte(hasselnott torte)
directions: Blend flour, baking powder and grated nuts together and set aside.
Beat eggs until thick and pale.
Gradually blend in sugar. Gently fold nut-flour mixture into the egg mixture.
Turn batter into 2 (8-inch) greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Invert pans and let layers hang until cool.
Remove from pans.
Fill with 1 cup sweetened whipped cream.
Sprinkle top of torte with confectioners sugar.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into loaf pans. Fill 1/2 from the top. Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: sly deviled eggs
directions: Butter a 9-inch casserole dish.
Cut the eggs in half and remove the yolks.
Mix them with melted butter, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, ham and scallions.
Blend until smooth.
Stuff the mixture into the egg whites.
Arrange the egg halves in the prepared dish.
Melt the remaining butter in a saucepan.
Stir in the flour to form a paste and cook for one to two minutes.
Blend in the milk and season to taste.
Heat until thickened.
Pour the sauce over the eggs and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over toasted English muffins.
Serves 6.

title: french drip beef
directions: Cover the cooker; start heat on high until it boils, then cut to low and cook all day, about 8 hours.
Add salt and pepper occasionally, but not too much.
Don't add water unless absolutely necessary.
Just before serving, shred the meat, using two forks. It should be tender enough to shred easily.
Serve on pumpernickel buns.
Top with hot mustard sauce (recipe follows).
(The meat can be cooked ahead of time and refrigerated in the juices.
Just take out and heat.)

title: beef brisket
directions: Place all ingredients into an oven cooking plastic bag and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: chess cake
directions: Cut
margarine
into
cake
mix;
stir in one egg.
Pat mixture
into
bottom
of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
It will be dry and flaky.
(Do not add more egg or butter than is called for.) Mix
powdered
sugar, cream cheese and three eggs; beat five minutes.
Pour
over
top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for
45 minutes, no more, no less.
Cut as soon as you take it from the oven.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Cut and cube chicken and cook (either fry or broil).
Cook alfredo noodles as directed.
Combine chicken and noodles in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chewy oatmeal squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 9-inch pan with Pam.
In mixing bowl, combine oil, brown sugar, applesauce and vanilla.
Add oats, walnuts, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix until blended.
Press mixture evenly into pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: awesome applesauce
directions: In a large pan use only enough water to cook apples until soft.
Nearly all of the water should have boiled out. You will need to stir frequently so it won't stick.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Mash apples and pour into sterilized jars with hot boiled lids.
If they seal, no need to refrigerator.
If you prefer not to can the applesauce, you can put it in freezer containers.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Pour dry ingredients over margarine.
Pour peaches, cherries, blueberries or strawberries over all.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend sugars and softened butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Roll in small balls; press with glass bottom that has been buttered and dipped in sugar.
This recipe can be used in a cookie press also.
Baking time is 8 to 10 minutes.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan. Add sugar and cocoa; mix well. Add flour and baking powder. Last, add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 greased pan for 25 minutes. Cool and cover with aluminum foil before cutting into squares.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in 1 cup of water.
Run through food processor.
Add sugar.
While hot, beat in marshmallows.
Add jello.
When it begins to set, add the nuts, pineapple and celery. Let set up and cool.

title: pink fluff
directions: Cut cherries into quarters.
Fold all ingredients together and pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set before serving.

title: snowtime beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; pour off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, onion, herbs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine spinach with cottage cheese and remaining 1/4 teaspoon of salt.

title: hot tamales
directions: To make tamale, roll 1 tablespoon of mixture in 1/2 cup corn meal.
Continue to roll until all of mixture is used.
Soak corn paper in water to dampen.
Roll in corn papers.

title: arabic coffee-saudi
directions: In bottom of a Saudi coffee pot, place ground cardamom; set aside.
In a plain coffee pot, place ground coffee and water. Bring to boil and continue to boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour through a strainer into Saudi coffee pot.
Let coffee and cardamom stand for 1 minute before serving.
Serving Size:
16. Preparation Time:

title: double berry coco punch(mauve color)
directions: In
blender
container,
puree
thawed strawberries and cream of
coconut
until smooth.
In large bowl or jug combine strawberry
mixture and cranberry juice.
Just before serving, add club
soda.
Garnish
with fresh strawberries if desired. Can serve slush frozen or over an ice ring or ice cubes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Beat eggs and add salad dressing, cheese, celery soup and onions.
Mix with drained broccoli.
Place in casserole.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dutch kitchen apple pie
directions: In saucepan, mix applesauce, salt, flour, sugar and spices. Stir and cook over moderately low heat, about 15 to 20 minutes or until thickened.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon filling into shell.
Combine sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over filling.
Roll out pastry and put over pie.
Seal edges and prick top.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Cool pie for 20 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar and cream to a smooth paste.
Glaze top crust.
Serve warm or cold.

title: spiced tea
directions: Steep 1 family-size tea bag in boiling water with 2 cinnamon sticks for 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix in 5 quart pan pineapple juice, orange juice, sugar, water, and cloves.
Add 1 cup strong tea with 2 cinnamon sticks.
Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: momma lee's vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in ice cream freezer and finish with milk.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; mix all ingredients and chill.

title: poppy seed sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Combine remaining ingredients with potatoes.
Spread in buttered casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover, bake 10 more minutes.

title: italian dream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, butter and sugar together.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk and egg yolks to creamed mixture.
Add nuts, coconut and vanilla.
After thoroughly mixing, fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into three 8-inch layer cake pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with foil and bake in 350° oven until done. Let cool.
Slice in half and scoop out center part of potatoes, leaving enough potato to support the skins.
To the potato pulp, add butter, cheese and parsley.
Mix well.
Put mixture back into the skins; return to oven and bake until cheese is melted.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, applesauce and soda. Then add vanilla, fruit, gumdrops and dry ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in loaf pans in slow oven (300°) or until tester comes out clean.
It may take longer than an hour to bake.

title: chicken harvest soup
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add flour and cook on low to create roux.
Add more flour to get the pasty consistency.
Cook just enough to remove the raw flour taste.
Heat milk and bouillon cubes in double boiler until a "skin" of tiny surface bubbles forms on top.
Stir occasionally.
Whip in the roux a little at a time until desired thickness.
If you run out of roux before achieving desired thickness, make more and add accordingly.
This is the time to get the soup texture right.
If you wait to thicken, the soup will be lumpy and the noodles broken.
Remove from heat after thickening.
Move to another burner and add vegetables, spices and chicken.
Stir well.
Add raw noodles last.
Cook on low for 10 minutes, then turn off stove.
Let soup sit for 30 minutes as chicken and noodles finish cooking.
Stir gently with a wide spatula to avoid breaking the noodles.
If the starch in the noodles renders the soup too thick, thin with milk or half-and-half.
Reheat and serve with hot yeast rolls.
Recipe can be halved.

title: coconut raisin pie
directions: Mix these ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: oatmeal-fudge bars
directions: Heat oven
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix
brown
sugar, 3/4 cup margarine, the eggs and vanilla.
Stir
in Bisquick and oats until uniform consistency. Heat
chocolate
chips,
milk, 2 tablespoons margarine and the salt
in
2-quart
saucepan
over
low heat, stirring constantly, until
smooth.
Stir
in nuts and vanilla.	Press about 2/3
of the
oatmeal mixture with greased hands in pan. Spread
chocolate mixture
over oatmeal layer, drop remaining oatmeal mixture by tablespoonful on the top.
Bake until light brown,	about
30 minutes;
cool
completely.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1-inch.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift together and set aside in a large bowl, the flour and sugar.
In saucepan, bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil. Add to the flour and sugar; mix.
Add the eggs, cinnamon, buttermilk, stirring lightly with each addition.
Add soda and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost with Sheath Cake Frosting.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Gradually add the buttermilk to the mayonnaise, mixing slowly until smooth.
Add the other ingredients and stir well.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours before using.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and margarine by hand until coarse. Add eggs, milk and raisins. Batter should be on the thick side. Put in greased pan. Pat top of bread with wooden spoon to smooth (if dipped in water, spoon won't stick to dough). Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Butter top when done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans with bacon, salt and pepper.
Combine milk and soup; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into casserole. Pour rest of onions over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange sauce
directions: Grate orange or tangerine rind in blender; set aside and grind the oranges in blender.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Boil until skins pop, then simmer 5 minutes or so.
Stir occasionally. If not quite sweet enough when you taste it before simmering, add a little more brown sugar.

title: hache
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven.
Pepper and salt stew meat. Brown meat in margarine.
Remove stew meat.
Bring margarine to boil; add the water 2 ounces at a time.
Cover with a lid after adding water.
Repeat this step.
Add bay leaves, cloves, cut and sliced onions and meat.
Simmer on low heat until meat is tender. Before serving, remove bay leaves and cloves.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute garlic in oil in large skillet, or small Dutch oven pan. Add paste, water, sauce and seasonings and mix well.
Simmer 4 hours for best taste, adding water if sauce gets too thick.
Or can be used after simmering for minimum of 1/2 hour.
Use more of seasonings for personal taste.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line Pizza Pan with cookie dough. Cook according to package and let cool.
Second layer:
8 oz cream cheese softened add 1/2 to 1 cup confectioner sugar.
Top with fruit:
Sliced apples, (soak in lemon water to keep from peaches-peeled)
Strawberries, grapes, kiwi, and bananas.

title: butter mochi
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder, then pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After cutting, roll in potato starch.

title: butterscotch banana pudding
directions: Mix milk with pudding mix.
Beat well with mixer.
Mix sour cream and Cool Whip with pudding mix.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Repeat.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries, whole orange and apple through food chopper. Add sugar.
Mix well.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: almost fat-free lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour oatmeal in hot water and let stand for 20 minutes if using regular oats, less if using quick oats.
Mix all the other ingredients and then add oats.
Set oven to 325° and cook in oiled or "Pamed" 9 x 9-inch pan for around 35 minutes or maybe more (keep in mind this is a very moist cake).

title: hot spinach dip with toasted cheese pita chips
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Add the milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Serve warm with pita chips.

title: overseas favorite fudge
directions: Heat sugar, milk, corn syrup and salt until sugar dissolves. Cook without stirring to soft ball stage (236° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, but do not stir. Cool to 110°.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Beat furiously until fudge is stiff and it begins to lose its sheen.
Add almonds continuing to beat.
Pour in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan; cool.
Cut into small squares.
Makes about 3 dozen depending on size.

title: chicken country captain
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and brown in fat.
Brown onions and peppers in butter.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.
Place chicken in Dutch oven.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover tightly. Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve chicken over rice and cover with sauce.
Garnish with currants, parsley, almonds and chutney. Makes 8 servings.

title: meat and pasta casserole
directions: Cook pasta; drain with cold water. Transfer to ungreased 2-quart baking dish. In a mixing bowl, beat sour cream and cream cheese. Stir in the chives, salt and pepper. Spoon over pasta.

title: easy marshmallow four layer bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and water until blended.
Pat into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes.
Layer marshmallows, candies and peanuts over crust. Bake 2 or 3 minutes or until marshmallows begin to melt.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Blend chocolate, butter and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in pecans, vanilla and flour.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cut into squares.

title: mrs. mot's "green stuff" congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions and let congeal until consistency of raw egg.
Mix remaining ingredients and stir into Jell-O mixture.
Chill until set.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Blend oil, flour, mustard, salt and pepper in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat 1 minute.
Stir in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and bubbles. Makes about 1 cup.

title: bombay turkey salad
directions: Cut turkey in 1/4 to 1/2-inch cubes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Blend other ingredients into mayonnaise.
Toss with turkey.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate covered ice cream balls
directions: Scoop ice cream into balls approximately the size of tennis balls. Roll ice cream balls in crushed Oreos, completely covering. Place on cookie sheet. Cover with foil and place in the freezer.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a pan, mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk.
Add one egg yolk at a time, while stirring ingredients over medium heat. Continue stirring constantly until filling thickens.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove and add butter, vanilla and coconut. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: soda biscuits
directions: Rub dry ingredients and shortening together to make fine crumbs.
Add milk, stirring with fork, until soft dough is formed. Roll 1/2 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm with butter or gravy.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into fourths and place in a baking dish.
Place onion slices over hot dogs, if desired.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour mixture over hot dogs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients like pie dough.
Add the eggs and soda which has been mixed in the milk.
Mix well.
Add the raisins, which have been cooked and drained, and the black walnuts.
Pat like hamburgs with your hands.

title: pop-up pizza casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in onion, garlic, oregano, salt, water, hot pepper sauce, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. In bowl combine milk, oil and eggs; beat 1 minute at medium speed. Lightly spoon flour in measuring cups.
Add flour and salt; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour hot meat mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour batter over cheese, covering filling completely.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until puffed and deep golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 servings.

title: so-good brownies
directions: Combine and bring sugar, shortening and water just to a boil in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat. Remove from stove. Stir in by hand the chocolate chips and vanilla until chocolate melts and is smooth; beat in eggs one at a time. Combine the flour, salt and baking soda and blend into the chocolate mixture. Add nuts if desired. Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9 metal baking pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jumbo meat balls
directions: Preheat the frypan to 325° until the light blinks out.
Mix all the ingredients except the shortening, tomato soup and water. Form 8 large balls from this mixture.
Melt the shortening in the preheated pan and brown the meat balls on all sides.
Add the tomato soup and water.
Cover and cook at 220° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: holiday cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, mix all ingredients.
Press into bottom and sides of a 12-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 500°. Watch carefully.
Do not allow to burn.

title: closet sweet pickles
directions: Fill
wide-mouth gallon jar with cucumbers.
Cover with distilled
vinegar.
Put
jar
in brown paper sack; set jar in closet for	6 weeks.
At end of 6 weeks, drain and wash cucumbers. Slice
very
thin;
layer cucumbers and sugar in gallon jar.
Put back in closet.
About once a week, shake jar until sugar is dissolved.	Place cucumbers in pint jars.
Cover with the syrup drained from cucumbers to which 2 or 3 drops of oil of cloves has been added.
You do not need to seal jars.	Five pounds of sugar is needed for this recipe.

title: shepherd's loaf
directions: Brown ground beef, add onions, green peppers and cream of mushroom soup.
Let simmer.
Cut top off of bread and remove bread, leaving shell.
Add bread to meat mixture.
Pour mixture into French bread shell and top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese melts.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up sausage links; place on top (add optional ingredients now).
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour on top of rolls; sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves hearty 6.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased, shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken scaloppine with lemon sauce
directions: Place each chicken piece between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or a rolling pin.
Combine flour and pepper; stir well.
Dredge chicken in egg and then in flour mixture, shaking off excess flour; set aside.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagne(low-fat)
directions: Cook beef in saucepan with enough water to cover beef; drain off all water and fat possible.
Add spaghetti sauce to beef and bring to simmer.
Combine remaining ingredients, except lasagne noodles, for filling.

title: alpine chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and almonds. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour half the chicken mixture. Cover with slices of cheese; then pour in remaining mixture of chicken. Cover and bake 30 minutes at 325°; remove cover and bake 10 more minutes. Sprinkle sliced almonds on top and bake 20 more minutes. Serves 20. Freezes well.

title: dilled cucumbers
directions: In a pot, combine vinegar, sugar, water, salt and dill.
Bring to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over slices in a quart jar; close tightly.
Refrigerate.
Chill for 3 hours.
May be topped with sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: hershey bar with almonds pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell. Decorate pie with almonds and Kisses.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt together with hands. Take out 1 cup for top of cake.
Make a well in crumbs.
Add liquids and fold in.
Do not beat.
Pour in loaf pan or cake pan. Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes or the regular heat you use for other cakes.

title: calico fruit bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
In large bowl, combine all bar ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: savory meatball soup
directions: Mix ground round, egg, bread crumbs, chopped potato, onion, milk, 1 tablespoon parsley and the salt.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in oil in a Dutch oven until light brown. Remove meatballs; drain fat from Dutch oven.
Mix tomatoes (with liquid) and remaining ingredients in Dutch oven; break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add meatballs, cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside.
Cream the cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Add the cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture together and mix well.

title: spicy hot chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together until well blended.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet-n-sour pork
directions: Toss pork in flour and place in pan with oil, cook until brown. Add syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and water. Slice green peppers and onions in rings and place on top, cover and cook about 30 to 40 minutes, or until meat is tender.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: three layer pie
directions: Crust:
Mix oleo, flour, 3 tablespoons confectioners sugar and 1/2 cup pecans.
Line bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes until light brown.

title: candied fruitcake
directions: Use two 9 x 3 1/2-inch loose-bottomed tube pans or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans (or use one of each).
With pastry brush, grease pans well with softened butter or margarine.
Set pan on piece of brown paper and trace around edge and inside of tube, then cut out tracing and fit in pan.
Cut a strip the right length and width and fit around side of pan.
For loaf pan, cut bottom and all side sections separately.
Turn on oven; set at 275°.

title: marinated duck
directions: Cut ducks in half lengthwise.
Place in plastic bag in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over duck.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally.

title: omelet sandwich
directions: Cut edges off bread, then put 8 slices of bread on bottom of long dish.
Layer bread with cheese, then ham.
Cover with the other slices of bread.
Mix the eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard in a bowl, then pour the mixture over the bread, cheese and ham. Cover.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Excellent for breakfast or a brunch!

title: chocolate peppermint
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed for 30 seconds. Serve in a chilled glass.

title: peggy's sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs, stir in butter and vanilla; blend well and add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Mix well. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
No need to chill dough.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bottom of dish with vanilla wafers.
Mix pudding mix with milk.
Add sour cream and half of Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Line dish with vanilla wafers and layer of pudding.
Alternate wafers, pudding and bananas, ending with pudding and top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Place onion, potatoes, carrots, water and salt in a large saucepan.
Steam until all veggies are tender.
Remove from the heat; add spinach, garlic cloves and set aside.
Melt the butter over low heat in a small sauce pan.
Whisk in flour, and keep whisking over low heat five minutes.
Drizzle in the milk. Continue to whisk and cook until smooth and you have a nice roux. Puree the veggies in the cooking water; return the puree to the saucepan.
Stir in the white sauce (or just milk if you are making a lowfat version).
Adjust the salt and add the white pepper to taste.
Serve hot topped with a sprinkle of nutmeg.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in hot oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for basting and serving with 2 chickens.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine with chicken, salad dressing, onion, green pepper and salt.
Blend soup and milk.
Add all ingredients; turn into casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 425°. Brown top under broiler, if you wish.

title: hazel green pasty
directions: Make pie crusts.
Mix beef, potatoes, onions and seasoning in a bowl.
Put in pie crust and seal.
Puncture holes in top crust. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are done. Cover crust edges if they start to get dark.
Heat milk and add through a hole in top crust.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Some people include turnips, but I never cared for them.

title: pork and bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
In 3-quart casserole, put a layer of sliced raw potatoes.
Salt and pepper.
Next, add pork and beans.
Third, add a layer of hamburger and onion.
Pour tomato sauce over top and bake uncovered for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until potatoes are done.

title: baked pineapple
directions: This is all mixed in the dish it is baked in.
Beat the eggs. Add sugar, flour and pineapple.
Top with bread, cut either in cubes or fingers.
Pour margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until bread on top is browned.

title: chinese beef and rice
directions: Cook rice in hot oil over medium heat until golden brown.
Add salt, water, bouillon cube and soy sauce. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add rest of ingredients. Cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes more.
(May need to add a little more water.)
All water should be absorbed by end of cooking time.
If not, remove cover and allow liquid to evaporate. Yields 2 generous servings.

title: 10 day chunk pickles
directions: Three Days:
Fill cold pack container with whole cucumbers. Make a brine that will hold up an egg (10-quart pail brine).
Keep cukes in the brine; they may have to be weighted down.
Let stand 3 days.

title: sangria (red or white)
directions: Mix all but soda and sliced lemon and orange and chill.
Add soda just before serving.
Garnish with slices of lemon and oranges.

title: peanut butter icing(bake auction; delicious on wacky chocolate cake)
directions: Cream together oleo and Crisco.
Add vanilla.
Add 3/4 cup 10x sugar.
Start mixer slowly.
Mix all together.
Add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and mix.
Add peanut butter.
Mix until blended.
Makes enough for 2-layer cake or 1 (9 x 13-inch) cake.
If you like lots of icing, make 1 1/2 times the amount.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground meat, onions and bell pepper together.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil with shiny side down.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the chicken pieces with the soup, sour cream and peas, broccoli or cauliflower.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Cover with the bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until bubbles.

title: summer surprise dessert
directions: Use all fresh fruit.
Mix the brown sugar and sour cream together before gently adding and mixing to the fruit.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook until forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons butter.
Beat and spread on cake.
